@NODE "Mail.2" "Re: Zip Gadget"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 1998 12:37:41 +0000
Subject: Re: Zip Gadget

Hi Matt,

> How can I give my Blitz window a zip gadget while not allowing user
> window sizing. I want to minimise my window to it's title bar *only*.

The Zip gadget is actually called a 'Zoom' Gadget. You can create a
Zoom gadget with the #WA_Zoom tag. I've never used it myself but
it shouldn't be too hard to do.

WA_Zoom - ti_Data points to an array of four WORD's to be used
   as the initial Left/Top/Width/Height of the "alternate
   Zoom position and dimensions."  The presence of this tag
   item implies that you want a Zoom gadget, even though you
   might not have a sizing gadget.
   New for V39: if the initial zoom-box left and top are
   both set to ~0, then Intuition will give your window
   "size-only" zooming, meaning that zooming the window
   will not affect the left/top unless the window needs
   to be moved on-screen.

You'll have to work out the rest yourself, I don't know if AmigaOS
will do the "Zooming" for you but I guess what you really want
is an IDCMP Event that lets you deal with the Iconify code yourself.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://paulburkey.home.ml.org

