@NODE "Mail.8" "Re: WritePixelArray8 & WPointer"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 1998 16:22:44 +0000
Subject: Re: WritePixelArray8 & WPointer

Hi James,

> It seems that the original KickstartROM routines which NewWPA8 replaces
> actually have a bug in them that trashes the chunky source buffer, which
> is a big problem... so:
> Q: does anyone here know if the CyberGFX/Picasso RTG software, and any
> other graphics card drivers, fix this problem...

If you are using CyberGraphX or Picasso96 then any calls to the
graphics library functions will be redirected to use the CGFX/P96
versions. This means that when you call AmigaOS WritePixelArray8
with CyberGraphX, it won't actually use the AmigaOS function at all.
Instead, it'll use the graphics card version. In the case of
CyberGraphX and Picasso96 I can reasure you that such a bug does
not exist.

> Q: does anyone know how to make the pointer on a screen you open from
> Blitz display in high res?

I tried to find out about this problem last time it was brought
up but I couldn't work out how to do it. sorry.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://paulburkey.home.ml.org

