@NODE "Mail.17" "Re: WPointer"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 1998 17:12:30 +0100
Subject: Re: WPointer

Hi James,

>   does anyone know how to change the handle/hotspot on the mouse pointer
> in an OS window? It seems that WPointer doesn't take into account the
> handle of the shape you send it?

If that is the case then you could try using the OS call for setting
a pointer:

SetPointer_(Window, Pointer, Height, Width, XOffset, YOffset)

Window is something like Addr Window(win#)
Pointer is something like Addr Sprite(spr#)

then XOffset/YOffset should be the hotspot and Height/Width are
obvious.

Cheers,

Paul

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.18" "WPA8 and AGA"
Date: Thu, 02 Apr 1998 10:00:09 +0100
From: James Marshall <homegrown@eclipse.co.uk>
Subject: WPA8 and AGA

Hi,
  just to clarify a few things... WritePixelArray8 DOES work with AGA,
but you DO have to use the temp rastport. However, it worked for me
setting the temp rastport to be the same as the original rastport. It
didn't crash for me when no temp rastport was set, it just didn't
display anything. If you use NewWPA8 from Aminet (util/boot I think),
you no longer need to specify a temp rastport. I suspect if you are
using a graphics card you also don't need to use a temp rastport, hence
Paul Burkey's code (which I believe was developed with a graphics card)
doesn't work on an AGA machine. Another good reason for using NewWPA8 is
that the ROM WPA8 has a bug that trashes the source chunky buffer when
you call it, which can be VERY annoying! Paul Burkey tells me that this
problem is not evident when using WPA8 with a graphics card.
  But anyway, WPA8 is stupidly slow on AGA, and although the problem is
marginally improved by NewWPA8 it's still going to be of limited use to
AGA users (at any rate for any program requiring regular screen refresh)

    James

--
Homegrown Software - Independent Amiga Games Developers
Web - http://www.eclipse.co.uk/homegrown
email - homegrown@eclipse.co.uk




