>Hello all.
>I've got three questions today

>One: Why does WJAM not work? I've tried all kinds of methods, but all I
>ever get is forground colour text, with the background blanked out in
>background colour. (I'm am using BitMapOutput)

WJam works for windows only - not for printing on Bitmaps.
For better control of bitmap printing, use the FNS fonts & commands.

>Two: I use the long version of Screen, and Then open bitmaps like this.
>Screen 0,0,0,320,256,8,0,"GameScreen",0,0 [what do these last
>two figures do anyway?]
They are the colours of the text pen and background pen for the screen.

Try substituting:

;Bitmap 0,320,256,8
;showbitmap 0
ScreensBitmap 0,0

>How come when I use PPaint to 'grab' the screen, all it grabs is the
>blank screen with the bar at the top, and not the bitmap?

Not sure, I am able to grab my program screens OK in PPaint - I think it will
only grab the Screen's bitmap, though.  If the screen's bitmap is 0, then it
will always grab bitmap 0, no matter if you are showing bitmap 1 or something.

