@NODE "Mail.26" "Re: WJAM/Grabbing screens/Diskplay"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 1998 19:59:31 +0000
Subject: Re: WJAM/Grabbing screens/Diskplay

Hi Curt,

> In my game, I open the screen, then use ScreensBitmap for my first bitmap.
> Then I create a second bitmap for the double-buffering, and open an
invisible
> full-screen window so I can read the mouse, change the pointer, etc.

Ahh, I would guess that the Screens Bitmap is the one that is
grabed by PPaint. I think it's impossible for the other bitmap
to be grabbed. Screen grabbers will always grab the ScreensBitmap
and using ShowBitmap would not change it. ShowBitmap doesn't seem
to alter the real ScreensBitmap but it manages to fake the fact
that the bitmap has changed.

Cheers

