@NODE "Mail.27" "Re: Windows"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 05 Mar 1998 10:30:38 -0600
Subject: Re: Windows

Hi Daniel,

On 05-Mar-98, Daniel Allsopp wrote:
>Hi,

>I'm currently creating a small text reader in Blitz. I use a window on
>workbench, but how do I get this window to open with the intuition style
>scroll bars on the right and bottom of the window. I've got the space at the
>bottom and right sides with the flags. Should you open the window with tags??
>Does anyone know the tags for this? Iknow it's possible cause the RIShape
>Editor uses them and that was made in Blitz.

>I'm curreny using a GTScroller gadget on the border would it be sensible to
>wblit shapes of the intui scrollers onto this??

I made something similar to this to be used as an online help system.
What I did was put all the text into list, then used a GTlistview gadget which
fills the window.  This gives you the  scrollbar & arrows and they work
automatically.
You don't even need to check for GadgetHit or anything.  Just make the
GTlistview so it fills your window.

I can cut my code for this out of the program and send it to you if you think
it will help.

I also gave my window a cycle gadget for selecting subjects (specified by the
text file) but this is optional.

Oh, it has a word-wrapping routine and can use any font (within reason) too.

If you want this, write to me direct.

Bye...
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



