@NODE "Mail.30" "window"
          (Post.Office MTA v3.1.2 release (PO203-101c)
          for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Tue, 24 Mar 1998 21:32:07 +0000
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 1998 21:28:56 +0000
From: Dave <d.boaz@virgin.net>
Subject: window

Hi
   I have a problem with the window command in a function.
   It worked ok out of the function, but in a function if I use
   all the windows parameters, when the function ends I get a
   crash or a message saying illegal instruction.

   This only happens when I do this

   statement whatever
     window 0,0,0,100,100,$flag,"Title",1,2,0,0
   end statement
                                              ^
   If I don`t use the last parameter there is no problem
   But I want to use it because I am using a superbitmapwindow.
   I thought maybe a register gets trashed which shouldn`t in
   a function, how could I fix this problem.
   It wouldn`t be a good idea to do a `movem.l` before and after
   would it?
   Anyone else had this problem?


Thanks for any comments

Dave


@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.31" "Re: window"
    26 Mar 98 10:24:36 0
From: "David Mcminn" <MD.BE4.Student.eee.rgu.ac.uk@eee-student.eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 1998 10:24:26 GMT0BST
Subject: Re: window

On 24 Mar 98 at 21:28, Dave opened wide and rumbled:

> Hi
>    I have a problem with the window command in a function.
>    It worked ok out of the function, but in a function if I use
>    all the windows parameters, when the function ends I get a
>    crash or a message saying illegal instruction.
> 
>    This only happens when I do this
> 
>    statement whatever
>      window 0,0,0,100,100,$flag,"Title",1,2,0,0
>    end statement
>                                               ^
>    If I don`t use the last parameter there is no problem
>    But I want to use it because I am using a superbitmapwindow.
>    I thought maybe a register gets trashed which shouldn`t in
>    a function, how could I fix this problem.
>    It wouldn`t be a good idea to do a `movem.l` before and after
>    would it?
>    Anyone else had this problem?

 I think I had a problem when I done stuff with AppIcons. The window 
command may change one of the variable base registers (a4 or a5). Try 
stopping the program before calling the window command. Check the 
values of a4 and a5 before and after the call to window. If there is 
a problem put this line before the window command

MOVE.l a4,-(a7)	; Or a5 instead of a4

and this one after the window command:

MOVE.l (a7)+,a4	; Or a5 instead of a4

.oO David McMinn Oo.
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-
*A1200T 1.3Gb 16xCD*
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-


