@NODE "Mail.33" "Re: Web Thingy"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 1998 23:38:50 +0000
Subject: Re: Web Thingy

Hi Alvaro,

> Can anyone tell me what commands a Web Server uses? I need to know the
procedure
> for logging into a Web Server, changing a directory, and then Grabbing a
certain
> document. Can anyone give me a quick low down on how to do this? I know all
the
> TCP stuff, I just need to know which commands to use when in the Web Server!

It's all fully documented on my Net-Link page. Just go to:

http://burkey.home.ml.org/netlink.html

Then follow the link to RFC1945 (the 6th link on the page). Theres
a html version for online browsing and a text version that allows
you top easily save for off-line reading.

The basic GET command is something like:

"GET <document> HTML/1.0"

This will tell the web server to end you the document/picture.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://burkey.home.ml.org

