@NODE "Mail.36" "Updated blitz-os page"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 02 Apr 1998 00:09:09 +0000
Subject: Updated blitz-os page

Hi,

I just updated the blitz-os support site. It now has information
on 15 libraries, 648 functions, 329 Newtypes and 4200 constants.
The best part is the complex set of links between each of these
elements. All AmigaOS structures are shown with links to the
equivelent newtype and each element of the newtype has links
to other newtypes that may be used. All AmigaOS tags are listed
with their values and many of them are commented. This takes up
close to 2meg of html with oer 600 files and over 2000 links.
Theres plenty of room for error and thres a bit of tidying up
to do. If you spot any broken links or any bad pages let me know.

The url for the site is..

http://burkey.home.ml.org/blitz-os

Another thing, if theres any library you'd like to see added
to this site I'll get it included for the next update. There
are lots of small libraries to add but I'm stuck for choice :)
I won't add the MUI library becaue it's already very well
supporting with it's own Blitz Lib. I might add the bsdsocket
library but it's quite big!

Some things to add to this site will be AmigaOS Macros, details
of the registeres and offsets for each function. Oh, and also
some examples for the important libraries.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://burkey.home.ml.org

