@NODE "Mail.40" "ToolTypes"
From: Luca Carminati <toffi@spm.it>
Date: Mon, 04 Sep 1995 12:35:46 -0500
Subject: ToolTypes

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.

This message was composed on an Amiga using the YAM mailer.
YAM is available at http://bitcom.ch/~mbeck/

--BOUNDARY.6455.2340.135242960.3

Hi Blitzers,

I'm trying to use system functions to read the icon tooltypes instead of =
the
RIToolTypesLibrary since this last increases the executable size of about=
 12K.
I think this code should always be used if you are interested in having
smaller executables. Here it is:

--------------

WBStartup

*Icon.DiskObject=3DGetDiskObject_(ProgPath$)
If *Icon
  a.l=3DFindToolType_(*Icon\do_ToolTypes,"MODE")
  If a Then MODE$=3DPeek$(a)
  a.l=3DFindToolType_(*Icon\do_ToolTypes,"FONTNAME")
  If a Then FONTNAME$=3DPeek$(a)
  a.l=3DFindToolType_(*Icon\do_ToolTypes,"FONTSIZE")
  If a Then FONTSIZE.w=3DVal(Peek$(a))
  a.l=3DFindToolType_(*Icon\do_ToolTypes,"XPOS")
  If a Then XPOS.w=3DVal(Peek$(a))
  a.l=3DFindToolType_(*Icon\do_ToolTypes,"YPOS")
  If a Then YPOS.w=3DVal(Peek$(a))
  FreeDiskObject_ *Icon
EndIf

s$=3DMODE$+"|"+FONTNAME$+"|"+Str$(FONTSIZE)+"|"+Str$(XPOS)+"|"+Str$(YPOS)=


EZRequest s$

End

--------------

The problem is that it works perfectly on 68020+ machines but it causes a=

system failure (guru $80000003) on A500 with 2.1 or 3.1 Workbench. It see=
ms
that somewhere the code tries to access odd addresses. I've attached the
source and the executable too. Is there anyone who can tell me where the =
bug
can be?

-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

