@NODE "Mail.41" "Re: ToolTypes"
From: Luca Carminati <toffi@spm.it>
Date: Mon, 04 Sep 1995 12:00:15 -0500
Subject: Re: ToolTypes

On 22-Mar-98, Paul Burkey wrote:

>Hi Luca,

>> The problem is that it works perfectly on 68020+ machines but it cause=
s a
>> system failure (guru $80000003) on A500 with 2.1 or 3.1 Workbench. It =
seems
>> that somewhere the code tries to access odd addresses. I've attached t=
he
>> source and the executable too. Is there anyone who can tell me where t=
he
>>bug
>> can be?

>What version of the icon.library is installed on the A500?

It is the right version since I coded the same in asm (using Devpac inste=
ad of
Blitz) and it works.

>Does the guru appear after only the GetDiskObject_() call or
>doed it only happen when you call the FindToolType_() function?

>Does it still guru if you remove all the lines that read the
>value in... 'If a Then ?.w=3DVal(Peek$(a))' etc..

>These are just a few last resort things. The code you
>provided as so clean, tidy and well written that I can't
>think of anything else that could be a problem :)

>The thing that first made me think about this was the fact
>that in only fails on pre 020 machines. Could this have anything
>to do with 'odd' memory reads? Maybe one of the OS functions
>is written to work with even memory locations and so fails when
>running on an 000 or 010.

In fact also the following code causes the same guru only on A500 machine=

---

  WBStartup

  If GetIconObject(ProgPath$)
    MODE$=3DFindToolValue("MODE")
    XPOS.w=3DVal(FindToolValue("XPOS"))
    FreeIconObject
  EndIf

  End

---

Is there anyone in the list who has got an A500 and wants to test the abo=
ve
code?

-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

