Date: Sun, 22 Mar 1998 17:53:42 +0000
Subject: Re: ToolTypes

Hi Luca,

> The problem is that it works perfectly on 68020+ machines but it causes a
> system failure (guru $80000003) on A500 with 2.1 or 3.1 Workbench. It seems
> that somewhere the code tries to access odd addresses. I've attached the
> source and the executable too. Is there anyone who can tell me where the bug
> can be?

What version of the icon.library is installed on the A500?

Does the guru appear after only the GetDiskObject_() call or
doed it only happen when you call the FindToolType_() function?

Does it still guru if you remove all the lines that read the
value in... 'If a Then ?.w=Val(Peek$(a))' etc..

These are just a few last resort things. The code you
provided as so clean, tidy and well written that I can't
think of anything else that could be a problem :)

The thing that first made me think about this was the fact
that in only fails on pre 020 machines. Could this have anything
to do with 'odd' memory reads? Maybe one of the OS functions
is written to work with even memory locations and so fails when
running on an 000 or 010.

