This is EXCELLENT!  I think it would be quite useful, even if it does take 5
minutes.  After all, you would be using it on the "finished" program, to do
some optimization.

Of course, it's even better if it can be faster.

All I know about a tokenized Blitz source is each command is represented by by
one or more characters >126.  Other than that, it is the same as a normal text
file. 


                                    Yours electronically,
