@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.44" "Tokenized"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 1998 21:00:06 +0100
Subject: Tokenized

Hi,

Does anyone know the format of the Blitz source file? I've
written a program that scans through the ascii version of a
Blitz program and it cretes statistics based on the commands
and libraries used. For example, using a small test program
it gave me this kind of report...

RIMiscLib.obj 5132b <- size of lib
    OpenFontPrefs        1 <- call count
    CloseFontPrefs       1
    DefaultFontHeight    1

ElmoreSysLib.obj 2448b
    ScreenWidth          1
    ScreenHeight         1

ElmoreDosLib.obj 7968b
    MoreEntries          1
    EntryName$           2
    Examine              1
    Run                  3
    Assign               1

And so on........

I think it'll be very usefull to help track down the libs
used. If for example I was to replace the two calls to
ElmoreSysLib.obj with a couple of AmigaOS system calls i
could save some valuable exe size.

It takes 18 seconds to scan through the 16k test program which
isn't too bad but its took over 5 minutes to scan through
the source code of Foundation! If I convert the parsing routine
to use Blitz Tokens it'll probably speed things up 30 times
at least.

Cheers,

Paul

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk

