@NODE "Mail.51" "Re: the outer limits"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Tue, 03 Mar 1998 14:38:20 +0100
Subject: Re: the outer limits

Hi Erick,

> How do I limit the mousearea on a screen in AmigaMode? 
> (MouseArea only works in Blitz mode)

I'm not sure if it's the best way but you may ant to try
the following code:-

*r.Region=NewRegion_()    ;<- you need to use amigalibs.res
*r\bounds\MinX=x,y,x2,y2  ;>- enter your limits here

Then when you open your screen, add the following tag:-

#SA_DClip,*r

I use this in the RTG version of Founation because the
RTG version uses a

> How do I prevent a Shape from exceeding the limits of a
> BitMap? (giving a "coordinates outside of BitMap" error)

Either use ClipBlit or check your coordinates before each
blit. It depends what you're trying to do.

Cheers,

Paul

