@NODE "Mail.52" "Re: the outer limits"
	(Debian Smail-3.2.0.100 1997-Dec-8 #2); Wed, 4 Mar 1998 10:06:22 +1100 (EST)
From: Rodney Norton <rodneyn@aic.net.au>
	Erick Ritmeester <eritm@xs4all.nl>,
	blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie
Date: Wed, 04 Mar 1998 10:10:40 +1000
Subject: Re: the outer limits

On 03-Mar-98, Erick Ritmeester couldn't help but dribble:

Erick,


>How do I read what option was selected with the GTCycle button?
>(I couldn't find any documentation or examples on that :-/

Typical of the manual...  Dob't stress I had to ask someone too...  Once you
know it's easy !  :)

>For instance:


>GTCycle 1,28,120,33,70,15,"",0,"option 1 | option 2 | option 3"

>Assumed that for instance "option 3" is visible, how do I pass 
>this selection to the program?

Okay, lets assume that this gadget is called #GADCYC1, okay !

So we do:

mode = 0   ;initial variable state.  Not really needed but it                 
   
           ;helps clarify the situation.
repeat
ev.l = waitevent

   select ev

      case $40  ;Gadget UP
         select gadgethit
            case #GADCYC1
            mode = eventcode
         end select
   end select
forever

Now, mode returns the code for the cycle gadget, 0 = option 1, 1=  option 2, 2
= option 3... So...

Somewhere later on you can do a case Mode 0, mode 1, mode 2, or the usual IF /
End If conditions, ie if mode = 0...... End if...

Okay ??!?!





RodderZ
