@NODE "Mail.58" "Re: Text edit"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 1998 21:12:38 -0600
Subject: Re: Text edit

Hi Oliver,

On 10-Mar-98, Oliver Marks wrote:
>Hi,

>I have written a program that loads in html code and displays it can
>anyone tell me how i can put a pointer in a window and how you can
>edit stored text so that you can add new charcters and take existing
>ones away.
>I am loading the code into an array and displaying it using nprint.

I am guessing you mean put to put a cursor in the window?
I think the commands "Edit$" , "EditFrom", "EditExit", and "EditAt" are what
you are looking for.  Have a look at these in the manual - yes, in this case
it actuallty DOES give a pretty fair explaination!
Edit$ actually only inputs characters, but it can be made to exit and give a
return code if a non-printing character is pressed, so you will need to add
your own routines for delete, backspace, etc.

-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



