@NODE "Mail.87" "Sell the Amiga"
Date: Sat, 21 Mar 1998 09:12:32 +0100 (MET)
From: Computer City <info@compcity.nl>
Subject: Sell the Amiga

Dear All,

The title of this message is just to get your attention - don't take it
seriously, however this message is just about doing that - selling the Amiga...

First let me introduce myself, my name is Ron van Herk and I am manager at
Computer City, not the US one, but the Dutch one, and we are Benelux
distributor for Amiga International.

Now to the point: Recently here in The Netherlands and also in several other
countries there are more and more smaller Amiga dealers starting. These
consist of newly-started companies or PC shops very carefully taking on the
Amiga in their product range. We have had many questions from our dealers
(and we're certain that this goes for dealers in other countries too) about
demo-software which can be run in a showroom demonstrating the Amiga's
capabilities. The problem is that there is none, at least as far as we know
of. The only thing we have is an OLD demo which even shows a rotating
Commodore logo. We also spoke to Amiga International, but they too have no
demo software. There used to be a demo-script which showed the Workbench and
the Amiga Magic software a bit, but that's old, too.

Since I have been a (quiet) member of the Blitz list for quite some time, I
was wondering if it was a good idea to create a demo just showing off what
our Amiga can do. Imagine a cheap 1200 in a showroom amongst Pentiums or
Macs. Visiting customers should say "Wow! what's that!?".

What would be perfect would be a demo that:
-Is based on the 1200 (later to be adjusted for other models)
-Is harddisk installable
-Shows the graphic, sound, multitasking and other capabilities
-Show how the standard workbench works
-Shows some game screenshots
-Shows video capabilities
-Has all texts in seperate files so local distributors/dealers can translate it
-Is freely downloadable from Aminet or the Amiga website

Of course, it could also say "This is what you can do with Blitz!" or
something alike.

It would be a great development push for Blitz if the users of the Blitz
list could offer it as gift to Amiga International, I think. And of course
it would be a great gift to the Amiga itself...

Don't let me be misunderstood, of course we are also looking for a cheap
demo to run in our store, I will be the last one to deny that. But we also
love the Amiga and want it to be promoted in as many ways as possible. And a
"shop-demo" is something that is needed very much...

What do you think?

Best regards,
Ron.


