@NODE "Mail.98" "Re: Scroller Gadgets"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 09 Mar 1998 00:41:52 -0600
Subject: Re: Scroller Gadgets

Hi Oliver,

On 07-Mar-98, Oliver Marks wrote:
>Hi,
>I am having trouble with Scroller Gadgets again can anyone help
>My problem is that I want make scroller gadgets like you get on the
>window borders when you view the contents of your hard drive 
>Propgadets look nothing like them and gtslider and gtscroller do not
>display the arroms at the bottom of the screen also they are not
>highlighted when you select the window which they are attached to.

To attach arrows to a GTscroller Gadget:

asize.w=16                  ;size of arrows in pixels

GTtags #GTSC_Arrows,asize   ;attach arrows to the scroller

(make GTscroller gadget here)

I don't know of any way to make gadgets change colours when the window is
activated.  You might try playing with the GadgetPens command, but I don't
know if this works on GT gadgets.




-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
