@NODE "Mail.101" "Re: ScreenTags & Autoscroll"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 1998 12:01:36 +0000
Subject: Re: ScreenTags & Autoscroll

Hi Mathias,

> I want to open with the ScreenTags command. This is an exemple :

> ScreenTags> 1,"Title",#SA_Width,1040,#SA_Height,800,
              #SA_Depth,8,#SA_AutoScroll,True,#TAG_DONE,0

> Bitmap 1,800,400,8
> ScreensBitmap 1,1

ScreensBitmap will 'create' a bitmap using the bitmap of the currently
opened screen so the previous 'Bitmap 1,800,400,8' is not needed in
this situation.

> Window 1,20,50,1,1,0,"",1,2
> ; Is it really necessary to open a window ?

Opening a Window of size 1,1 seems a bit pointless unless you're
using it to set things like the Pointer or you're using funtions that
require a window for things other than a display.

> The result is not very good because the pointer come by the left side
> when it goes after the right border.

I think you have to specify some Overscan settings.

> A solution is to use #SA_LikeWorkbench tag, because this tag contains the
> missing parameter. But what is this parameter ? I don't want to use all
> the caracteristics of the Wb.

You should try the following tags.

#SA_Overscan
#SA_DClip

I've never used these tags so I'm sorry I can't explain how
they work. They are covered in the Blitz OS page on my web site
if you don't have the Autodocs it's probably worth visiting
the page and chcking the intuition.library/OpenScreen_ funtion.

http://burkey.home.ml.org/blitz-os

I'll finaly upload the new pages tonight. I've added lots of new
libraries including cybergraphx, ted, icon, iffparse, asl, xpk,
locale and even the ahi.device docs.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://burkey.home.ml.org

