@NODE "Mail.103" "Re: Screen command"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 18:26:28 -0600
Subject: Re: Screen command

Hi Dennis,

On 18-Mar-98, Dennis de Haan wrote:

>Hi There Blitzers,

>I'm having some trouble with the screen command... I'm opening a screen
>using this screen command:

>Screen 0,8,"Screen Name!"

>The screen opens perfect on my a1200 AGA machine, but i'm getting messages
>from beta testers of my program that they are having trouble opening this
>screen...

>Anyone have a screen command or a sollution for non AGA machines???

I have not used the short version of the screen command, but it looks to me
that you are asking for an 8 bitplane (256 colour) screen?

This is impossible on a non-AGA Amiga.  ECS and OCS support only 6 bitplanes.


-- 
