Hi Kenneth,

> I've run into bit of a problem lately, and i wonder if any of you guys could
> help me with it.... How on earth do you save a bitmap/picture as a
> GIF/JPEG/PNG ??? I now how to load them, but NOT how to save them...

You'll have to do a bit of research for jpeg or gif although
I'm sure it's not hard info to track down. I'd imagine GIF to be
very easy to impliment once you have the information. I think
jpeg will be very tricky but you should do a search for
"Independent JPEG Group" on the web.

As for png, I think this might be it on Aminet.

PNG-guide.lha docs/hyper 77K PNG specification (AmigaGuide format)

It's a shame there are no datatypes for writing files as well
as reading them. I'm sure it would be a nice project to make
if anyone wanted to create a system like that.

