> 
> 
> Q. Where are Acid Software?
> A. Simon Armstrong has long since left the Amiga market. The
> last I heard he was doing some work for Codemasters. The
> label 'Acid Software' is now owned by Guildhall Leisure.
> The Ultimate Blitz CD which is now in the shops had 0
> involvement with Acid Software - they were paid a royalty
> for each copy sold. NOTE: The *entire* Blitz Support Suite
> was put on this CD, WITHOUT our knowledge or consent.
> We have received 0, zilch, nothing, from the 500 or so
> sales of this CD (and hence, the 500 lost sales of BSS).
> For sales of BSS (legitimate) we received 6 ukpounds
> per copy. For this Ultimate Blitz CD which has lost
> us 500 sales, we were offered nowhere NEAR
> that much (clue <1 ukpound) so we have some
> things to 'sort out' with Guildhall.

Please accept my apologies - I had been intending to buy BSS for
ages, then when I saw Ultimate Blitz in the shops I assumed you
were involved. I then ran the install script and realised that 
it was just someone chucking some stuff on the CD and calling
it Blitz.

So that's 5UKP I owe you...
