here is a solution from me (perhaps some people agree on the list).
why dont we go two steps further and create a completely new programming
interface (perhaps with some nice things we know from blitz).
the third step would be calling it not blitz basic, but calling it different.
the reason is obvious. no rights for blitz. and with the introduction of 
the ppc processor with his completely different design than the normal 
68k and his os, things have to be done completly new. so why should we 
hang around with old stuff ???? (also when naming the new language, we 
should not call it basic, since many people were laughing when you told 
them you were programming in blitz BASIC :)


