@NODE "Mail.133" "Re[9]: Make a much more powerfull Blitz 2"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 1998 23:32:31 +0000
Subject: Re[9]: Make a much more powerfull Blitz 2

Hi Julian,

> > Yes, the size is impresive. I wonder what's in the Windows lib that
> > makes it so big. It would be nice if we could decide on some commans
> > o remove from Blitz. What I mean is remove the Window and Screen
> > command and force us all to use the Tags opions. This is just one
> > example of how we have unnecessary functions in acidlibs. It would
> > be nice to have two acidlibs, one strict (small minimal) version
> > and one large flexable version.

> The Window and Screen commands are for Kickstart 1.3, the tag commands are
> for 2.0+ .  As for writing two different versions of acidlibs, wouldn't the
> time be better spent working on Phoenix?  If it could be done quickly
> though, it would be handy.

It's not a case of writing two acidlibs. It's a case of compiling
one acidlibs file with all functions an one without the unnecessary
functions. Simply remove some useless functions from acidlibs.

Cheers

-- 
