@NODE "Mail.136" "Re[7]: Running blitz with a 040"
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Fri, 06 Mar 1998 13:15:31 +1200
Subject: Re[7]: Running blitz with a 040

On 05-Mar-98, Paul Burkey wrote:
>Hi Anton,

>>   The last version I have is V1.6; in ConnectTCP it only closes the
>lib
>> if a TCP stack isn't running, but it should also close it in CloseTCP
>> otherwise it never gets closed if there *is* a TCP stack running.

>Okay, maybe I missunderstood the way opening libraries works.
>This is the code (in a simplified way).

>SocketBase.l=OpenLibrary_("bsdsocket.library",0)
>If SocketBase=0
>  Function Return False
>Else
>  CloseLibrary_(SocketBase)
>  Function Return True
>EndIf

>So I presumed that if OpenLibrary returns 0 then there's nothing
>to close but if it returns a non zero then there's something to
>close. Have I got things mixed up here?
 
   Nope, it was me in the end :-s  I used TCP_FuncsV1.5 as the base for
my UDP_Funcs and didn't put in the CheckTCP bit properly into my connect
routine :-s 
   Boy do I feel silly :-S   Oops, I'm real sorry about that, it was a
massive waste of time!

  Seeya- Anton  

-- 
