Date: Tue, 31 Mar 1998 01:29:37 +0000
Subject: Re[7]: Make a much more powerfull Blitz 2

Hi Fr=E9d=E9ric,

> same library. So, there is one .obj for NewScreen commands and one othe=
r for
> NewWindow commands. The result is impressive too. The Window.obj has th=
ese
> commands and take only 390b when compiled :

I noticed your commands don't have any error chcking. For example
I creted a small program:

NCloseWindow(0)

When I ran it with error checking on it GURU'ed. This is fair enough
when I compile with error checking off but it's not very good durring
the development stages.

>     * NWBox
>     * NWPlot         ; This one is 20% faster than the old function !

These two don't work with CyberGraphX. Are you using the graphics.library=

for these funtions?

>     I think this would be easy to convert all the window related blitz2=

> commands into new format. Wait and see... For now, I create a 800b prog=
gy
> which find the WBScreen, open a window, draw a plot and a box, wait a
> mouseclick, return windowheight/width and quit. Try to do it in standar=
t
> blitz2 format and you will see a massive 13kb proggy ;-)

Yes, the size is impresive. I wonder what's in the Windows lib that
makes it so big. It would be nice if we could decide on some commans
to remove from Blitz. What I mean is remove the Window and Screen
command and force us all to use the Tags opions. This is just one
example of how we have unnecessary functions in acidlibs. It would
be nice to have two acidlibs, one strict (small minimal) version
and one large flexable version. =


Cheers

