> Thanks for all the help on this.  Unfortunately, the real problem turns out
to
> be that the WPA8_ command appears NOT to be able to work on an AGA system.
> I tried your example, and it does the same thing as my code - opens an empty
> window, then the program hangs...

ohh, maybe it's a problem with having the source data in fast ram. I used
a 'cludgy' array system for the example but it's probably better to use
something like AllocMem to reserve the memory and poke the numbers into
it. The AllocMem command can reserve memory in fast or chip.

