@NODE "Mail.149" "Re[5]: Next Generation of Blitz"
          Mon, 30 Mar 1998 00:27:34 +0200 (MET DST)
From: Peter Thor <thor@mailbox.swipnet.se>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 1998 00:28:15 -0500
Subject: Re[5]: Next Generation of Blitz

Been following the editordiscussions, and i must really say that i strongly
support the idea of a new editor with tokenized formats, different colours for
proc/functs etc.

I think the editor should be enhanced in EVERY way with more powerful
searchmethods with better patternmatching, format selections, bookmarks and
hotkeys, formatting of paragraphs etc, macros.. the list goes long. A nutshell
with a CLI-based compiler is really a smooth and proper way to use it. As Paul
said with a GUI who might become linked to your favorite editor if you want
that to happen. Its really flexible to have a powerful standalone GUI possible
to compile and debug the sourcecode undependant of a special editor.

So my suggestion is to leave TED and move on to a standalone compiler/debugger
etc.

//Thor
