@NODE "Mail.151" "Re[5]: New ChunkyCPU Blit command planned"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 01 Apr 1998 16:52:30 +0000
Subject: Re[5]: New ChunkyCPU Blit command planned

Hi NUEL,

> > This is still the problem.  I am trying to put Chunky 2  (a blitz chunky
> > "object") into my window 0.  I tried everything I could think of for the
> > pointer to the chunky array - the following is the only way it will compile
> > for me without a syntax error:

> It'll never work !!! Sorry Curt, but you always need a Bitmap for the
> WritePixelArray8 !!! In fact you need 2 Bitmap !!! One attached to the first
> RastPort and an other attached to the second RastPort :-(

No, WritePixelArray8 has nothing whatsoever to do with Bitmaps
of any type. It's a "chunky buffer to window" function. Bitmaps
don't come into it at all! Okay, so maybe somewhere in the
structure of the windows rastport there are references to bitmaps
but this is all done for you when you make your window.

When you open a window you'll have all of the necessary objects
setup for you including Layers, Bitmaps, Rastports, Menus,
Gadgets, Fonts etc.. ALL of this is done for you so theres no
need to get into the messy details if you need to.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://burkey.home.ml.org

