Hi Paul,

On 17-Mar-98, Paul Burkey wrote:
>Hi Curt,

>> I didn't know that was possible.  I remember getting an "Array already
>dim'd"
>> error, but that may have been on my old Apple][.

>Theres an exact same error in Blitz but it doesn't seem to be
>a problem any more. According to the Blitz 2.1 manual the error
>is this:

>*Array already Dim'd:* An array may not be re-defined

>so why does this work with no problems....

>Dim name.s(3)

>name(0)="Paul"
>name(1)="Curt"
>name(2)="Bob"
>name(3)="James"

>Dim name.s(1)

>name(0)="Paul"
>name(1)="Curt"

>Dim name.s(4)

>name(0)="Paul"
>name(1)="Curt"
>name(2)="Bob"
>name(3)="James"
>name(4)="Peter"

Aha, another change they didn't bother to put in the manual!  In fact,
comparing my old Blitz 1.7 manual to the 2.1 manual, I see they are exactly
the same!  Except the 1.7 manual had more examples and such...

Yes, the sad truth for those who complain about the Blitz manual  (that's ALL
of us, isn't it?) is that the manual was actually better before they "updated"
it for 2.1.

In fact, I think a better manual should go at the top of the list of requested
improvements for Blitz.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
