@NODE "Mail.160" "Re: Re[4]: Sorting files"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby@inetnebr.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 10:24:21 +0500
Subject: Re: Re[4]: Sorting files

On 18-Mar-98, Curt Esser flashed:

>Aha, another change they didn't bother to put in the manual!  In fact,
>comparing my old Blitz 1.7 manual to the 2.1 manual, I see they are exactly
>the same!  Except the 1.7 manual had more examples and such...

>Yes, the sad truth for those who complain about the Blitz manual  (that's ALL
>of us, isn't it?) is that the manual was actually better before they
"updated"
>it for 2.1.

>In fact, I think a better manual should go at the top of the list of
requested
>improvements for Blitz.


  Sounds like a project that some of us could get rolling.
I propose that we collectively write a new Blitz manual from the
storehouse of knowledge here in us.  I would be happy to actually do
the writing and formatting.  We could discuss each of the commands and
reach a concensus on what each one does and when and how it works and
should be used.  We could also come up with clear and complete
examples for the useage of each command.
  I further propose that we begin with a core of the most used and
needed commands so that the 'manual' could begin to be used by
neophytes in the Blitz realm right away.  I remember how hard it was
for me just to figure out how to get a picture on the screen in some
of the modes when I first started Blitz 2.
  We could release the text as a free E-book on Aminet and continue
to improve it over time.  We could also offer it to whoever makes the
next upgrade of Blitz Basic as a starting place for their new manual
and/or we could offer to continue developement of it for them either
to help the project or for a share of the profits.
  I have thought for a long time that a better manual was needed and
even for those of us more well versed in B.B. it could be very helpful
to have all of our knowledge pooled in one easily understood and
organised document.

  As I said, I would be happy to make the actual document if those of
you here would be willing to give it a go.  If I get a positive
responce I will begin right away.


     Regards,
               Donovan Reeve (bubby@inetnebr.com)





