From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 1998 21:54:48 +0000
Subject: Re[4]: RWE and Blitz - do we own it?

Hi Fr=E9d=E9ric,

> > *AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Message\mn_Node\ln_Pri =3D pri
> > *AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Command  =3D #CMD_WRITE
> > **AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Data     =3D *p1
> > *AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Length   =3D length
> > *AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Offset   =3D 0
> > *AHIio\ahir_Frequency       =3D #FREQUENCY
> > *AHIio\ahir_Type            =3D #MY_TYPE
> > *AHIio\ahir_Volume          =3D $10000    =

> > *AHIio\ahir_Position        =3D $8000       =

> > **AHIio\ahir_Link            =3D *MyLINK
> > SendIO_ *AHIio
> =

>     It's my code no ? ;-)

Yes, I have about 6 different Blitz versions of the ahi_play
code. Each is very slightly different but yours was the closest
to the original AHI version so it was useful to show my point
about Blitz/C compatability :)

While we're on the subject of AHI, if anyone wants to do
the Frequency bit all they need to do is replace the like:

*AHIio\ahir_Frequency  =3D #FREQUENCY

with:

*AHIio\ahir_Frequency  =3D 3579440/<Blitz Sound Period>

Cheers


-- =

