On 03-Mar-98, Paul Burkey wrote:
 
>>   Ahh, it actually is, in ConnectTCP{} (V1.6), with OpenLibrary_().
>> Blitz doesn't automatically close any libs opened with
OpenLibrary_().
>> If I don't do a CloseLibrary_() on the bsdsocket.library, Miami
>refuses
>> to quit saying "Miami can't exit: some applications refuse to close
>the
>> Miami libraries."

>As I said in h last mail. It does open the library but a few
>lines below it closes it again. Doesn't it close it properly? 

  The last version I have is V1.6; in ConnectTCP it only closes the lib
if a TCP stack isn't running, but it should also close it in CloseTCP
otherwise it never gets closed if there *is* a TCP stack running.

Seeya- Anton 
 
-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
      



