their way around who would REALLY be pissed if the Pheonix package
didn't work as is when they got it but rather required them to purchase
another expensive program which they didn't know where to get or how
to use.(whew) #;u)>  That sounds like something Microsloth would pull.
  No, we obviously can't release Phoenix without an editor in the
