editors. Next we see if we can arrange a deal with one of the
manufacturers for a liscensed version at a good cost which we would
include in the package WITH all of the necessary scripts, etc for
making it work with Phoenix.  That way new users would have a complete,
ready-to-use package with all the trimmings and all our editor team
would have to do is plan the features to add and make the scripts.

