Ah, but there's nothing to stop such things working in editors like GEd, or
BED or CEd etc.  All they really need is a decent ARexx port (and the ones
I've just listed have that) and you're off.

It would be (relatively) straightforward to create an ARexx script which
checks which word the cursor is on and sends that off to the online help
search program.

Another feature that doesn't need to be tied to one particular editor. :)


