@NODE "Mail.173" "Re[4]: Icons"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 01 Sep 1997 22:22:11 +0100
Subject: Re[4]: Icons

Hi David,

> > The icon image stucture stuff is in the autodocs...
> 
>  I'm sure there is an example on one of the BUMs (by a member of RWE) 
> which takes an icon and displays it on the screen. I think that the 
> commands used were included in one of their libraries.

The RI ToolTypes Lib contains the icon.library commands. It has
commands such as IconToShape, ShapeToIcon, SetIconType, PutIconObject
and 16 other commands. The lib comes with BSS but I'm not sure
if it was ever available as freeware.

An alternative would be to convert the icon.library fd file
to a Blitz lib and use it direct.

Cheers,

Paul

