@NODE "Mail.174" "Re[4]: BlitzPPC?"
From: Andreas =?iso-8859-1?Q?H=E5kansson?= <andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 1998 21:36:37 +0100
Subject: Re[4]: BlitzPPC?


>Blitz could be the userfriendliest PPC language around.
>RWE would earn lot of money if they are fast. How  many
>BLitz users would buy it? How many new  users  would it
>gain? Thousands? Millions? ;)

Well I doubt that there are many blitz  programmers that
has a ppc card yet (I'm  one  of  the  lucky ones, brag, =

brag :). That  would  by a PPC only  version, but if RWE
made it like we have been talking about, with the choice
to generate code to both cpus (by selecting which cpu to
generate  code  for in  the  Compiler  Options), then  I
belive that many blitz  programmers  would  by  the  new
version, since they would be  able  to make PPC versions
of thier software, even tough they dont have  a ppc them
self.

If we look beyond the present blitz users, I  think that
is blitz gets  the  ppc  support  before  anyother basic
language, it  would  get  MANY new  users (a big part of
them being people that use AM*S today), since  it  would
give them the  same  possibilities  as  mentioned  above
(making  ppc  version of thier  software, regardless  if
they have a ppc card them self). Itr would  also attract
the people that  wants  to  start to programm, since  it
support the next generation  of amigas, and isn't out of
date.

Damn we need to get  acid  to hand  over  the rights for
blitz to RWE. AM*S has been handed over  to someone that
will try to give it  life  again, and  give  it  a major
face lift, and if blitz dont  want  to  get stuck in the
past (and behind AM*S), then  blitz  will  also  need  a
face lift. And giving it PPC  support  asap  will  be  a
step in that direction.

What ever happend to tha suggestion that we should write
a well phrased and informed  email  to acid (or who ever
owns it), and explaine to them that  they  have  to hand
over the rights to the source code to RWE, if they  want
blitz to survive, and make any  money of it??? Was  that
idea killed? I think  we should  send  such  e-mails  to
them frequently (not regulary, since  that  woul d be to
obbvious). I'm  prepared  to write the  e-mail (I  would
first send it to the list to get your  oppinion about it
of course) and send it to them. If we decide to do this,
then I think everyone should  list what  they  think  we
should have in the email and we can vote  about it. This
way everyone gets a  say what we  should write. What  do
you guys think of this?

 ByE!



