I think this is a good idea.

I think the most important additions needed is:

The PPC & processor support already discussed

GFX card support!  There should be some sort of automatic GFX card routin=
es,
so the bitmaps, shapes, etc. would all be converted to chunky format & se=
nt to
fast ram if a GFX card is in use so all the normal bitmap commands could =
be
used (BBlit, etc) no matter which system the program is run on.

Or if this is impossible, at least have GFX card versions for all the bit=
map
commands.

Personally, I think these two are much more important than limiting the
finished exec size (as was discussed before) -
After all, did any of you not try the Doom conversions because of the hug=
e
file size of the .wad files?

This is 1997, after all - we (and the Amiga) must look to the future and =
not
worry so much about supporting the past.  Who do you know that runs a 1 m=
eg
system with no hard drive any more?


                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



