If I'm not much wrong the pentium still have those 8 registers,
that the 486 have. And those extra MMX CPUs have some special registers, =
I
think.

The more registers the chip have the more complex the busrouting in
the instruction unit(s) have to be. And if the CPU is CISC typed then it
will make every instruction much more complex due the complex fetching an=
d
load/store operation included to the instruction.

