It'll never work !!! Sorry Curt, but you always need a Bitmap for the
WritePixelArray8 !!! In fact you need 2 Bitmap !!! One attached to the fi=
rst
RastPort and an other attached to the second RastPort :-(

>Window 1,winx,winy,winwid,winhi,$800,"",1,0        ;temporary rastport??=
?

I'dont do it like this, and I don't know if it works .... here's my metho=
d :

tmprp.RastPort=3DAllocMem_(SizeOf.RastPort,#MEMF_ANY|#MEMF_CLEAR)
InitRasport_ tmprp

Now, you need to open a temp bitmap :

*bm2.BitMap=3DAllocBitMap_(((width+15) LSL 4) LSR 1,1,depth,#BMF_CLEAR,0)=


;width =3D the width of your picture
;depth =3D the depth of your picture

tmprp\Layer=3D0
tmprp\_BitMap=3D*bm2     ; Attach the temp bitmap to your temp rastport.

>Window 0,winx,winy,winwid,winhi,$800|$1000,"",1,0  ;viewing window
>rp.l=3D   Addr Window(0)                             ;rastport pointer

Arghh :-(  rp.l isn't the address of you window !!!

rp.RastPort=3DRastPort(0)

>chunk.l=3DAddr Chunky(2)         ;this is wrong, I know - but what for t=
his??

I don't know how is handle a Chunky object , but it can work... =


You need to attach the picture's bitmap to the first rastport.

rp\_BitMap=3DAddr_of_your_picture's_bitmap

>count.l=3DWritePixelArray8_ (rp,0,0,winwid,winhi,chunk,tmprp)

And now, free the temp bitmap and rastport

FreeMem tmprp,SizeOf.RastPort
FreeBitMap_ *bm2

I haven't time to test if my code work, but i think it could ;-)


>Or is what I am trying to do not possible?  This is for a standard AGA
machine
>without a GFX card.  (and maybe it would work on GFX cards too?)

I really don't think you can use the ___PixelArray8 commands without the =
use
of bitmap.

