  Right.  That is just what I meant.  In fact I believe I mentioned
that a little further down in the same post.  The compiler and the
compiled code don't need the numbers so why have them.  Then we are
free to give the libs any alpha-numeric name we choose as long as
no two are the same.  And if we give them names describing their
functions there is almost zero chance of any two ever conflicting.


  Perhaps the rest of you can analyse this idea and make sure we
aren't overlooking any important points.


   Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)  NEW ADDRESS





