@NODE "Mail.203" "Re[2]: RWE and Blitz - do we own it?"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 1998 02:23:05 +0000
Subject: Re[2]: RWE and Blitz - do we own it?

Hi Steven,

> How about creating a language which uses the structures of C but just
> represents them differently.

I think Blitz already does this. It's only a matter of a simple
convertion to convert simple 'C' to Blitz. Just take a look at AHI
for a good example:

AHIio->ahir_Std.io_Message.mn_Node.ln_Pri = pri;
AHIio->ahir_Std.io_Command  = CMD_WRITE;
AHIio->ahir_Std.io_Data     = p1;
AHIio->ahir_Std.io_Length   = length;
AHIio->ahir_Std.io_Offset   = 0;
AHIio->ahir_Frequency       = FREQUENCY;
AHIio->ahir_Type            = TYPE;
AHIio->ahir_Volume          = 0x10000;
AHIio->ahir_Position        = 0x8000;
AHIio->ahir_Link            = link;
SendIO((struct IORequest *) AHIio);

Becomes...

*AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Message\mn_Node\ln_Pri = pri
*AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Command  = #CMD_WRITE
*AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Data     = *p1
*AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Length   = length
*AHIio\ahir_Std\io_Offset   = 0
*AHIio\ahir_Frequency       = #FREQUENCY
*AHIio\ahir_Type            = #MY_TYPE
*AHIio\ahir_Volume          = $10000    
*AHIio\ahir_Position        = $8000       
*AHIio\ahir_Link            = *MyLINK
SendIO_ *AHIio

Appart from Blitz's very limited range of data types and a few
other missing variable/data/structure features you can see that
the two languages are very similar. Blitz is by far the most
comfortable of the two to work with.

> Infact, just a rework of C this would make importing and exporting
> of C easy.

The more features we 'lend' from C the easier it'll be to port from
one to the other. If we can keep Blitz's simplicity and it's solid
traditional syntax (For..Next While...Wend etc..) then we can't
go wrong.

Cheers,


-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://paulburkey.home.ml.org

"Russia Elects Cobweb."
-- The Day Today




