Hi MinuteMan,

> > Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))=FrontScreen
> 
> With ActiveScreen it works fine now, thanks! But it seems I
> dont have the "FrontScreen" command ?!?
> Is there another way to check that my screen is the frontmost?

Thats odd. The FrontScreen command is part of "screenslib.obj"
which is part of the AcidLibs file. It's the same library that
contains the commands:-

Screen, SMouseX, SMouseY, ShowScreen,
ViewPort, ShowBitMap, CloseScreen, ScreenTags

and many others..

If you don't have that library theres something wrong!!

Cheers,

Paul

