@NODE "Mail.214" "Re[2]: Object Addr's"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 1998 17:50:29 +0100
Subject: Re[2]: Object Addr's

    Hi Paul
 =

>> If you do not use any commands from the windowslib but have a line =

>> like x.l=3Daddr window(0), does the windowslib get stuck into your exe=
?
> =

> No, the Addr Window(0) function is not part of the windows lib.

    Hummmm, I'm not sure. Window(0) is part of the lib window else why my=
 exec
size goes from 500b to 8000b when I add this command ? Simply because it
link the whole Window.lib. It's my problem because I can't do my window
related function if I can't get the addr by a other way...
 =

> But how can you possibly have a Blitz Window without using the Windows
> commands to open one?

    Yes. It's easy to do...

    Use the system function :

    *MyWin=3DOpenWindowTagList(....)
    if *MyWin
        Winaddr.l =3D addr Window(0) ; It will be the window 0
        poke.l Windaddr, *MyWin    ; Fill the Blitz 2 Structure !

        ; Your program. It should work.

        CloseWindow(0)
    endif

    Regards,

        Fred

