This is a very nice idea.

>  I've used the OS GTGadget routines and would use them for more 
> complex stuff, but if I'm writing a simple program then I'd probably 
> prefer to use the Blitz GTgadget commands.

If you're doing this to avoid the additional 12k of windowslib
then make sure you don't use the commands WaitEvent, Event, GadgetHit
MenuHit, ItemHit, SubHit, EventQualifier and EventCode.

Depending on what the program you're making will be doing it could
be easy (or hard) to avoid all these.

