@NODE "Mail.217" "Re[2]: Next Generation of Blitz my contribution"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 1998 17:26:16 +0000
Subject: Re[2]: Next Generation of Blitz my contribution

Hi Steve,

> >>  *OS* *Programing*
> >>  --------------
> >>  Paul Burkey, which I  think sould be a Workgroup Leader, if
> >>  he want to.
>
> What does OS Programming actually mean?

I'm not too sure myself ;) I think we're actually talking about my
plans to provide a set of Blitz targeted Autodocs. Slightly TOO
similar to the AmigaOS autodocs but with the emphasis on Blitz
coding. The whole project will be based around a batch process
that reads through the real Autodocs and creates a new version with
Blitz structures, Blitz examples and easy links from one function
to another. When you see the word 'RastPort' it'll have a link to
the RastPort structure in blitz as well as a link to the Blitz
documentation on the RastPort() command. This could be a link to
a simple RastPort() explanation or to the RastPort() entry in the
"New Blitz manual". Most of this can be done in less than a days
work (when I can find a spare day!) but the examples and improovements
will be dealt with once it's working.

I plan to deal with the exec, intuition, graphics, dos and diskfont
libs first but theres no reson why versions for locale, bsdsocket,
muimaster, rtgmaster and many others can't be added at a later
date.

I'll have to find out about the legality of this type of project
due to copyright restrictions on the AmigaOS autodocs. I'm not
planning to simply re-publish the autodocs with extra links and I'll
probably leave out a hell of a lot of functions for simplicity.
It's possible that the project could be an off-line only system that
requires the original autodocs available for instilation.

Cheers,


-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://paulburkey.home.ml.org

"Arse!"
-- Fast Show



