You probably won't find it in any search but here it is:

http://burkey.home.ml.org/blitz-os

if you have any probs just add /index.html to the end of that :)

I'll add a link and make the page more official when I've added
more Blitz based info. At the moment it's slightly too close to
the original Autodocs so it must have a low profile for now.

The page covers over 700 functions in 15 libraries/devices. It
also includes docs on cybergraphics.library and ted.library as
well as exec, icon, iffparse, graphics. dos, xpk, ahi, intuition,
datatypes, asl, amigaguide and more.. :)

For GFX ard support you should really read up on:

graphics.library

  WritePixel_
  WritePixelArray8_
  WaitBOVP_
  ScrollRaster_
  ClipBlit_
  BltMaskBitMapRastPort_
  WritePixelLine8_
  BestModeIDA_
  BltBitMap_
  ClearScreen_
  Draw_
  Move_
  ReadPixel_

These are all very simple to use once you get going. I guess BestModeIDA_
is a bit of a tough one but if you can master all of the above commands
you'll soon find the AmigaOS functions are no longer a problem.

