@NODE "Mail.242" "Re[2]: Detecting a shape hitting colours on a bitmap"
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 1998 18:27:25 +0000
Subject: Re[2]: Detecting a shape hitting colours on a bitmap

On 15-Mar-98, Curt Esser churned out *this* drivel:

> >  Does anyone know of a blitz function that will tell me if any part of 
> > my shape is touching a non-background area of a given bitmap?  I seem to 
> > remember using one before, but I can't find anything anywhere that sounds 
> > familiar. :(

Use " BlitColl (Shape#,x,y) "

Checks if any pixel is non-zero where your shape would be.

BlitColl checks the actual shape,rather than just the rectangular
area it uses.

Manual says it's fast,too...

Hope this helps,
-- 
James L Boyd

