@NODE "Mail.254" "Re: Re[2]: BitplanesBitmap....this is getting on my tits!!!"
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <samin@megabaud.fi>
Date: Mon, 09 Mar 1998 21:34:40 +0200
Subject: Re: Re[2]: BitplanesBitmap....this is getting on my tits!!!

On 10-Mar-98, Paul Burkey wrote:

> > BitPlanesBitmap db,6,%1111111 so you can render the shadow only once
> > and the original graphics can be rendered without altering the shadow=


> That is how you would make a 7 plane bitmpap, To make a 1 plane bitmap
> you'd use %10000000 which is hat you'll need if you want to render
> shadow effects.

Well you missed my point here. so I try to make it clearer. :)

so you have one bitmap with 8 planes
and you make the fake bitmaps so that you got 7 bitplane and 1 bitplane
ones. If you don't do the one bitmap (with 7planes) and you blit somethin=
g
the bits in the plane 7 (in planes 0-7) is set too so the shadow doesn't
survive from the blit. Ofcourse there might be situations where you reall=
y
want to clear the shadow, and you should then use the original 8 plane
bitmap.

> > The only drawback is (I think ) that it works VERY slowly on the
GFX-cards.
> Bitmaps won't work with GFX cards anyway so it's not an issue.

well in some cards they work trough conversion but its not an option when=

you are writing games, because the conversion slows it down VERY much.

