@NODE "Mail.255" "Re[2]: BitplanesBitmap - The FINAL installment."
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 02:32:41 +0100
Subject: Re[2]: BitplanesBitmap - The FINAL installment.

Hi Fr=E9d=E9ric,

> Your example is fine but it don't run at full speed on my A1230/50 16Mb=

> fast ;-). Why ?

What do you mean by full speed? If you remove the VWait it'll
run at 1600fps here. Put the WVait back at it runs at 50fps.

> Because the 'Use Bitmap bt+2' is REALLLY TOO SLOWWWW.

It's not that slow. I removed the Use Bitmap command and it
speeded up by 2%. The loop itself was so small that any command
would slow it down by this much. Replace it by somthing as simple
as a=3D0 and you'll see the same slow down.

I think the example was to show how the BitPlanesBitmap works
rather than how best to blit a 120byte image. If you look at a
proper game of todays standards you'll see 1000 times a much
graphic rendering and 100 times as much code executing in the
main loop. Now consider if it's such a problem that Use Bitmap
takes up 25000th of a second.

Cheers,

Paul

