@NODE "Mail.256" "Re[2]: Binaries"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 1998 04:01:00 +0000
Subject: Re[2]: Binaries

Hi BootBlock,

> > really don't mind getting binaries in my emailbox.  I have a 28.8k modem,
> > 15k from a POP server does not take up too much of my time.
> 
> Nope, I don't mind either. The whole point is to help each other out and
share
> code, so anyone feel free to email me those binaries with that luverly Blitz
> type code in `em!

The issue of binaries must be met by deciding on a size limit for
the mailing list. I think 15k is a prety good limit. 15k takes less
than 10 seconds on a mid range modem. It's not as if we get more than
one 10k mail each week. Another idea would be to setup your email
software to delete any incomming mails from the blitz-list above 10k.

There used to be a 4k limit on the mailing list which would bounce
any large postings back at the poster. Now we seem to be setup on
some kind of ye'ole-mailin'list system where features and automation
are a naughty word :)

Cheers


