@NODE "Mail.261" "ReRe: Keyboard input"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby@inetnebr.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 1998 15:16:40 +0500
Subject: ReRe: Keyboard input

On 12-Mar-98, Dennis de Haan flashed:
>On 12-Mar-98, Donovan Reeve wrote:

>Hi Donovan,

>> Help!
>>  For some dumb reason I can,t figure out how to
>>get a keypress character input in Blitz2.
>>  I tried useing the same method as in Blitz1
>>(the origional BB) but it doesn't work
>>(ky$=inkey$).  I only get the message "Can't
>>input character from Default Input".
>

>Try Edit$ for a change, this works fine, but needs a return after each
>input. You can also create an invisible window and use window input and
>the ky$=inkey$.


  The problem with edit$ is that I am using the keyboard as a control
consel in many of my games.  The player presses a key and gets the
desired reaction from the program.  I don't want them to have to press
return afterwards because that would take away much of the conveniance
and fluidity as well as confusing the player and slowing down their
reaction time.
  I will try your invisible window idea however I am worried about the
additional ram that will take and won't that only work in Amiga Mode?
  I need speed and I need to conserve ram as all of my games press the
Amiga to its limits.


    Thanks for the suggestions

            Donovan Reeve  (bubby@inetnebr.com)





@ENDNODE
