@NODE "Mail.277" "Re: Questions regarding OS gfx"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Wed, 04 Mar 1998 21:53:27 +0100
Subject: Re: Questions regarding OS gfx

Hi MinuteMan,

> 1. How do I check that my screen is the active one?
>    (ActiveScreen doesnt work, I get another address than the
>     one of my Screen)

Try this:

If Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))=3DFrontScreen

or replace FrontScreen with ActiveScreen. =


> 2. How do I change the mousepointer of my screen?

WPointer

You must have a borderless/backdrop window on your screen.

> 3. (Especially for Paul Burkey) How did you manage your pointer
>    is moving as fast as usually? The pointer moves very slow
>    and sometimes stops on my screen...

Maybe I was just lucky :) I don't do anything to speed
the pointer up in Foundation.

> 4. What=B4s the best way to create real shadows? At the moment =

>    I=B4m doing it this way:
>    I have a 256 color palette, the first 128 are standard and the secon=
d
>    128 are darker versions of my first 128 colors.

This is something that was discussed recently. The simple explanation
is to create a BitplanesBitmap containing only the last plane. Then
render to the last plane and bobs your uncle! If you need a better
explanation I'll repost an old article that contains more info.

Cheers,

Paul

