Hi Andrew,

> Could anyone with a knowledge of graphics cards tell me which would 
> be quicker on a graphics card:-  the WritePixelArray8_ command on a 
> 640x480 screen OR WritePixel_ for each pixel.

WritePixelArray8 woul be MANY times quicker.

> Heres the point:-  which would be quicker: plotting each dot as soon as
> the zoom procedure makes it to the screen, or render it to yet 
> another chunky buffer which could then be WritePixelArray8_ed to the 
> screen. (If double buffered it would be a quad buffer...Wow!)

Why not try option 3. ScalePixelArray_() which is part of CyberGraphX
and probably emulated by Picasso96 too.

> phew... and yes i know to expect a cup-of-tea interval slideshow.

There are mpeg viewers for CyberGraphX that play mpegs via the
ScalePixelArray funtion and they run quite smooth (approx 12fps)
with or without scaling in real time.

> Maybe when it works i can powerPCerise it somehow.

I think the ScalePixelArray function might use the GFX card
hardware to achieve the scaling on some boards.

Get the CyberGraphX developers kit from aminet for details.

