@NODE "Mail.288" "Re: Printing from blitz"
From: Luca Carminati <toffi@spm.it>
Date: Mon, 04 Sep 1995 13:09:29 -0500
Subject: Re: Printing from blitz

On 16-Mar-98, Adam Lounds wrote:

>Hi Y'all

Hi Adam.

>Just a quick one - how do I print out some text? =


>I've got 2 ideas:

>1. Write output as normal to prt: (can I use any filename?)

>or
>2. Write to a file and then do amigaDOS copy from file>prt:.

>Questions:

>Will 1. work? Do I just openfile and all the rest, then nprint each
>line? What filename do I use, 'cos I can't just open a file called prt:
>I think I can use any name, but not sure.

I tried the following and it works:

If WriteFile(0,"PRT:")     ; file name not needed
  FileOutput 0
  NPrint "Something......"
  CloseFile 0
EndIf
End

>What's the Blitz command to run a DOS command through Blitz? Do I use
>the _execute sys command, and if so, has anyone got any examples?

Try this:

Execute_ "Type S:Startup-Sequence >PRT:",0,0

-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

