@NODE "Mail.291" "Re: Print text letter by letter..."
	Wed, 18 Mar 1998 14:48:35 -0800 (PST)
From: BootBlock of Carnage <BootBlock@GeoCities.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 21:17:39 GMT0
Subject: Re: Print text letter by letter...

On 18-Mar-98, Tommi Nieminen wibbled:
>Hi.
>I have only one question: 
>How can i make text appear on a window letter by letter, like somebody 
>would be typing it?

Try this matey (I'm just typing this directly into YAM - but it *should* work
first time! :) :


   #REPEAT_RATE = 20  ;The higher it is, the slower the typing.

   MyString$    = "Oooh look! It's a nice little message, init?"+Chr$(10)
   MyString$    + "There's even a 2nd line!  Huzzah!"

   For CurrentPos=0 to Len(MyString$)
      Print  Mid$(MyString$,CurrentPos,1)
      Delay_ Rnd(#REPEAT_RATE)
   Next


