*A1200T 1.3Gb 16xCD*
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-


@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.293" "Re: Print text letter by letter..."
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 10:53:37 +0000
From: James Marshall <homegrown@eclipse.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Print text letter by letter...

Hi Tommi,
  just use a loop to cycle through your text string, printing one
character at a time...
e.g.

use window #output_window
for l1=1 to len(txt$)
    if asc(mid$(txt$,l1,1))=#newline
        nprint ""
    else
        print mid$(txt$,l1,1)
    end if
next l1

(can't remember what the ASCII value of a newline character is, which is
the value you should put in #newline)

Hope that helps,
    James

