> as blit, but offer much more power).

but fact is, that you cant mix binary froms..you cant use a 3rd party ppc 
lib from a 68K side. so you cant mix up those two structures.. :(
so we have here two different compilers .. one for the ppc which has to 
be rewritten and one for the 68k side. both being completly the same. so 
you need one workgroup who designs a completly new compiler for the ppc 
blitz which is compatible to the current one, and one team enhancing the 
current compiler.. i dont think this is a good solution. iw ould say, 
creating two teams/groups. one group enhancing the old compiler and one 
team/group designing something new for the ppc which has all the features 
of the blitz 68k compiler.

