@NODE "Mail.321" "Phoenix Development Facts."
From: Andreas =?iso-8859-1?Q?H=E5kansson?= <andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 1998 13:02:33 +0100
Subject: Phoenix Development Facts.


 Hello to you all,

Recently I have seen a long disscusion about  wheter or not
we should write a new  editor  for  Phoenix, or  make it so
that it works with any editor. The most  chocking statement
came from Julian  Kinraid, who said that we cant make a new
editor since we  dont have a clue on how the Phoenix system
will communicate  with Phoenix. This is true, for now.

I'm sorry if  I havn't  been  clear  about  this before, so =

I'll take it one more time, so everyone  will  get a chance
to understand. The Phoenix team HAS  been choosen, and work
has ALREADY  begun to plan things like  the  new  Compiler,
Debugger, library format etc. So  Phoenix  isn't  a  only a
dream  we  have. It's  actually  already  being  made  into
reality. =


Now I WONT  reveil  who  is  on the Phoenix Team, just yet,
since  they  would  get  bombarded   with  questions, about =

when's, how's and what's. This would only be very iritating
on the Team, as for the people that would have emailed them
since there isn't anything to reveil just  yet. You have to
remember that this is a big project, and  requires carefull
planning if we want it to be good. =


Nor will we give away  any developer   information. Why you
ask your self? Well the answer is real simple. Since we are
developing a completly new developer system, and  DONT want
the real juicy parts to be spread  all  over  the  net, and
perhaps straight into the hands of  some  other  developers
(a worst case scenario would be if the  developers  of AMOS
got info about this project). Stupid? I dont think so, have
anyone on the  list  heard about  any  software  developers =

reveiling thier tactics and golden cards? I think not.

I fully understand that  everyone  is  dieing to know whats
going on, and to you  I  will say  this. We  are  currently
working  our  ass of, to  get up a  Phoenix  webpage, where
all the news, releases etc will be put up. Now  this  isn't
empty promissig, infact a beta version of the web  site has
already been put up (and no, I wont give away the  URL just
yet). Once the new standars etc  starts  getting finalised,
the news WILL be posted on the webpage, once  it's finished
that is.

Now I could make you  alot of  promissis on how the Phoenix
system will work, and what it  will  have for features, but
you would only kill me if we changed anything, and it wasnt
the way I told you. I tell you this, keep  calm, and you'll
be suprised once the specs is reveild.

Final paragraph. How the heck can I tell you  all this? Why
should you belive me, I mean I  could  be full  of nonsence =

and false statements. Well the fact is, I have been choosen
to be the Phoenix Project Super Visor. If I  dont know what
I'm talking about, then who does (My  name  isn't  Petro T, =

thats for sure)??

Ohh yeah, one more thing. The mailing lists for Phoenix has
be created, but wont be open  for  the  public,  until  the
Phoenix consept has been worked out. There are two  mailing
lists setup for Phoenix. One for everyone, and  one for=A0the
Phoenix  developers. The s econd one, is  already  i n use. =

We'll tell you more about this, whem it's time to  join it.


 ByE!





@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.322" "Phoenix announcment"
From: Andreas =?iso-8859-1?Q?H=E5kansson?= <andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 1998 19:01:29 +0100
Subject: Phoenix announcment


 Hello All Fellow Blitzers,

As we all know the idea of a new language that supports blitz
100%  but also offers more power then blitz it self does, had
been getting a lot of positive reaction. And I'm  quite  sure
that  we  all can agree that the list has been very busy this
last week, with more then 60% off all mail that's been posted
to the list has consernd the above.

We have seen many good ideas been presented, which would make
this  new  language  very  powerfull, and proberbly a big hit
amongst new amiga programers, and people  that  already  uses
Blitz Basic or AMOS.

Well after a week of "behind the scenes" disscussion,  I  can
now  reveil  that  a  team  has  formed  that will leade this
project. The project and group has been given a name, and the
Workgroup  Leader  positions has been filled (all except one,
which I will tell you all more  about  further  down  in  the
list). And one other thing. We are setting up two new mailing
lists that will have to do with the new language. There  will
be  one  public mailing list, where anyone that wants to, can
join in, and be apart of the new language  disscussions  that
will  form.  This  is  the place where the new language team,
will get the ideas for the features that you as a user  would
like to see in the new language.

Then there will be a Developer Mailing list for the  project.
It's  on  this  list  where all the real coding stuff will be
disscussed among the project members, and a few lucky  people
that  will be alowed on to it. This list will be INVITE ONLY.
And people will manualy be subscribed.

As it is now, there are six people that forms the base of the
project, but we will reqruite more people when everything has
been setup, and are ready. The project  and  group  name  was
suggested  by  deuz72  (Sergio),  and  this will earn him the
right to a position in the group, and the  developer  mailing
list. For you who dont know what he suggested, I can tell you
that he suggested that  the  new  language  would  be  called
"Phoenix",  taking  the  idea  from the mithological firebird
which rebirth from the ashes. The group  name  will  then  be
"Phoenix Corporation".

The six people behind the base of the project is.

*Andreas* *H=E5kansson*
Project super visor.

*Steve* *Matty*
Compiler Workgroup Leader

*Paul* *Burkey*
OS Programing Workgroup Leader

*Alex* *Wingrove*
PR Workgroup Leader

*Donovan* *Reeve*
Manual Workgroup Leader

*Claus* *Herrmann*
PPC Compiler support leader (apart of the Compiler WG)

Now we  need  someone  to  be in charge  of  the  *New*  *Editor*
workgroup, so if you feel like you could leade the team, that
will work on a new and improved editor, then please email  me
directly,  and tell me why you should be selected. You should
code in asm or c.

Well this is what we can tell you this far. Please dont start
to  bombard  us  with tons and tons of email, wanting to know
more, since much is  still  in  the  planing  phase.  We  are
currently  working  on the agendas for each workgroup, and we
will let you know as soon as they are  ready.  We  will  also
tell  you  when  and how you can subscribe to the new mailing
list.

 Good ByE!

-- =

