@NODE "Mail.325" "Phoenix and the letter 'P'"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 1998 18:44:20 +0000
Subject: Phoenix and the letter 'P'

Hi,

One of the earliest languages was BCPL. The successor to that
language was called 'B'. Then C as given it's name becaue
it was the 2nd letter in BCPL. Many hardcore computer language
experts consider the 'next big thing' should be called 'P'.
C++ is a different issue because it was created mearly as an
upgrade to the existing language.

And so it becomes a refreshing coincidence that Phoenix has
such a close link with this rule. Sorry to bore you all with
this story but I thought it was amusing.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://burkey.home.ml.org

