 Hiya,

Well once more, here is a mail, with  summs  up  all  my  comments
about all the mail that is sent to me about this. It also contains
more of my ideas and suggestions.

>You have suggested the idea so you deserve the right to choose if
>you  want  to bee da super visor. You are a dedicated Blitz user,
>but do you have a stable net connection to  do  the  super  visor
>job?

Yes I would be glad to fill this post, as long as no  one  objects
to me being the workgroup super visor that is. I actually have two
stable internet connections. The one at home, and  one  at  school
(that  can  be  used if something happens my home connection...ohh
lets say huge internet phone bill :)

Well moving on. Since I  suggestion  the  workgroup,  people  have
started  involve them self even more. And I think we need to setup
this work system asap,  since  people  is  really  eger  to  start
working. Many people has stated that they want to be a part of one
of the mentioned workgroup, but since I get a ton of mail  nowdays
for  the  blitz  users, I dont have the time to read threw all the
mails again and extract what workgroup people want to  be  a  part
of. There for I'm asking the people that want to help, to email me
and tell me which workgroup they would want to be  a  part  of.  I
know  many  of you out there want to help with the new manual, and
I've read about many good ideas for it.

But promiss me one thing. Dont start work on it, until  the  *New*
*Manual* workgroup has been setup, since we will need to setup all
kind of guidelines etc. But what you can do now, is to gather  all
the  written  info  about blitz, that can be used when writing the
new manual (such as the manual in PostScript format etc). We  also
need  a  Workgroup  Leader  in this workgroup. Any suggestions who
this should be?

Someone also suggested that we should setup a PR Workgroup,  which
I  think  is a very good idea. To start with, they could take care
of the website, and keep it updated. And when  a  phase  has  been
finihed, and is ready for release they step in to promote it. Tell
the amiga mags about it etc. We'll also need  a  Workgroup  Leader
for this workgroup, so any suggestion are welcome.

Here is the current workgroup status:

  *New* *Compiler*
  -------------
  Steve Matty which I think should be Workgroup Leader, if he
  wants to. So Steve are you up to it?

  Erwan  Fouret  who wrote the EFMUILib with me. An excellent
  programmer, with good C and ASM skills.

  *OS* *Programing*
  --------------
  Paul Burkey, which I  think sould be a Workgroup Leader, if
  he want to.

  *New* *Editor*
  ------------
  No one at the moment.

  *New* *Manual*
  -----------
  Bob stifer. He suggested to me that we also could form
  sub teams of this workgroup, that work with translation
  of the new manual into diffrent languages. I think this
  is a very good idea. and among us, I'm sure we could
  translate it into quite a lot of languages.

  *Public Relation*
  --------------
  No on at the moment.

As soon as the workgroup has been formed, work can start.

 ByE!




