would
>have to be a wizard to beat GoldED!  In fact, I could write a plugin that
>tokenises Blitz commands...

  That would probably be very useful, If you can and have time, do it.

  What I had in mind though, non-dedicated editors wouldn't do such as on-line
command and routine-formating help.  You know, for dummies like me.  #;u)>

  I actually don't care how it's accomplished, I just want a very smooth and
helpful programming enviroment so I can spend my time writing my ideas into
code instead of trying to figure out how to write the code.  We are after all
supposed to be using computers to make things easier.  If I wanted to be told
that I had to do things according to the will of someone else I would be
using a Mac (inflexible as heck) or a MS-based machine (an indeciferable
mess).
 The Amiga invented user-friendliness and that is still the reason I stick
with it even though improvements are needed.  It wasn't Burger King that first
said 'Have it your way'.  In fact, the Aniga was invented precisely because
a few guys wanted to have it their way and were sick of corporate buricratical
limbo.

  Your points are very good and I think we are really desiring the same thing.
A good programing environment for a powerful and flexible coding system.


  Have a good one,

    Donovan Reeve (bubby@inetnebr.com)






