@NODE "Mail.380" "Re: Next Generation of Blitz"
From: Steven Wojciechowski <stevie-woj@boy-woj.demon.co.uk>
Date: 20 Mar 98 01:34:40 +0000
Subject: Re: Next Generation of Blitz

Previously in Life Andreas Hkansson(andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com) had this to say:
> *Phase1*
> In this phase a replacment to the current compiler should  be
> written.  New  features  should  be  implemented  as well, to
> attract the current blitz users to use it instead of the real
> blitz compiler. This complier should be written in such a way

What about the legal aspects of this?  By releasing an adjusted
version of the current compiler would this not leave you, legally
speaking, in the sh*t?
AFAIK, in order for a Blitz compatable to be released in anyway it
would have to be rewritten without any of the code from the current
complier (which Guildhall still hold the rights to).


> *Phase2* - *Phase5*
> Keep adding new support to things that the old blitz compiler
> doesnt support (and never will, since who will update it?).
> 
I don't think this part of the plan will be as productive as it could
be.  The main goal of the plan seems to be geared towards agressively
ousting out Blitz, which I think will prove counter-productive (and
*very* M$ like).  The emphasis should be placed on improving the
functionality of the language rather than making Blitz incompatable
with it.  If it is possible to do an evolution from Blitz then from
the start you should have a heavily structured plan of what the new
language will be, what it will support, etc.  Once you know the target
you can produce a 5/6 step plan of evolution.  If you just add bits as
you go you will end up with a language which is more of a patch work
than Blitz already is.


> Now to something completly diffrent from workgroup. We need a
> few things to be decided. A name for the committee (since The
> Blitz Committee found lame), and we also need a good name for
> the  "new  language".

Possible language names:
1. Red   - (after all, the mail from RWE motivated these actions)
2. B++   - ;)
3. B.G2  - Blitz. Generation2
4. G    - Generation2   (if your mailer doesn't show it properly, it
           should be G squared
I also liked the suggestion of "Magma"


Possible Committee names:
1. Blitz Developement Committee 
2. Blitz Developement Group


Alot of folk seem to be getting very excited at the prospect of
helping in the future of Blitz (including me) but in the rush to get
everything underway several obvious problems might not be noticed
until it's too late.  Remember, there's no hurry - a job worth doing
is a job worth doing right, yes? 

--
Stevie W. 
http://www.boy-woj.demon.co.uk/
stevie-woj@boy-woj.demon.co.uk


@ENDNODE
