@NODE "Mail.390" "Re: New Commands..."
From: "Julian Kinraid" <jkinraid@clear.net.nz>
Subject: Re: New Commands...
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 1998 12:16:54 +1200
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi Mr BootBlock,


[snip]

>While I'm here, does anyone know another way of FindScreen'ing the
frontmost
>screen using a ROM call?

*ibase.IntuitionBase = IntuitionBase

If *ibase
    ilock.l = LockIBase_ (0)

    *front_screen.Screen = *ibase\ActiveScreen

    UnlockIBase_ ilock
EndIf

*front_screen contains the front screen (well duh!)

If you don't have the IntuitionBase command, you will have to open
intuition.library yourself.

Ciao,
Julian Kinraid




@ENDNODE
