@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.396" "Re: New ChunkyCPU Blit command planned"
Date: Wed, 01 Apr 1998 12:27:54 +0100
From: James Marshall <homegrown@eclipse.co.uk>
Subject: Re: New ChunkyCPU Blit command planned

Hi Curt,
    Chunky(2) is a chunky object? What format is the chunky object? It should be a
x*y byte array, ideally. i.e.

Dim chunky.b(319,255) (for a 320 x 256 chunky bitmap)

Also, I don't think you should use Addr Window <n> to get the rastport. I think
the command you want is called RastPort, but I'm not quite sure.
Don't bother about a temporary rastport either, just set it to the same rastport
you want the output to go to.
This technique definitely works on AGA machines without graphics cards... I've
used it myself. It will work on graphics cards when used on a screen opened with a
valid graphics card ModeId, ideally supplied using ASLScreenRequest (as I've only
just found out).
    James

Curt Esser wrote:

> This is still the problem.  I am trying to put Chunky 2  (a blitz chunky
> "object") into my window 0.  I tried everything I could think of for the
> pointer to the chunky array - the following is the only way it will compile
> for me without a syntax error:
>
> Window 1,winx,winy,winwid,winhi,$800,"",1,0        ;temporary rastport???
> Window 0,winx,winy,winwid,winhi,$800|$1000,"",1,0  ;viewing window
> rp.l=   Addr Window(0)                             ;rastport pointer
> tmprp.l=Addr Window(1)                             ;temp rastport pointer??
