@NODE "Mail.397" "Re: New ChunkyCPU Blit command planned"
          Tue, 31 Mar 1998 13:48:18 +0100
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 1998 13:48:21 +0100
From: James Marshall <homegrown@eclipse.co.uk>
Subject: Re: New ChunkyCPU Blit command planned

Hi Curt,
  don't worry, I can do some basic ASM coding for one, and I'm sure there are
people on this list with more experience than me. If 2 or 3 people are prepared
to put a little bit of time into it I think it should be doable. Personally I
think the best option would be to implement a chunky bitmap library, rather than
a chunky to window library. I think the first option would probably be easier to
implement. You say we should replace BitmapToWindow, but I think
WritePixelArray8 would have the same effect, as it writes a chunky array of
pixels to a window. You can do all your graphics operations on the chunky bitmap
with the proposed new library.
  So anyone interested? I think we need someone with experience of creating
libraries (Christos?), and people with some knowledge of ASM. We should also
come up with a list of commands people would like. I can think of the following
that need chunky equivalents, off the top of my head:
GetAShape
Block
Blit
ClipBlit
QBlit
BBlit
Unqueue
Unbuffer
Scroll

Any other suggestions?
So, come on people... let's do something useful for Blitz!
    James

