@NODE "Mail.403" "Re: Multitasking"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 1998 20:20:43 -0600
Subject: Re: Multitasking

Hi Jake,

On 06-Feb-78, Jake Frederick wrote:
>Is it possible to make my blitz-mode game multi-tasking and OS friendly
>without drastically changing the code? What are the major limitations of
using
>Amiga mode to make a game?

Of course, the answer depends on how the code is written now.  :)

If you are using a lot of "Copper" tricks in your game this could be a
problem.

The major difference is that you have no sprites in Amiga mode (use shapes
instead) and no copper stuff.

As far as speed goes, unless you have a lot of cpu-hogging other programs
running at the same time, you will not notice a difference.


                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
