@NODE "Mail.406" "Re: Multitasking"
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 1998 09:59:00 +0000
From: James Marshall <homegrown@eclipse.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Multitasking

Hi Jake,
  basically in can be quite difficult... I've been experimenting with
various
methods and have just completed my implementation. Depending on the
style of your
game and what you require from it, you have several options.
First you need to replace all your DisplayLibrary calls with Screen and
Window
commands (set up a screen of the same size/resolution/depth, with a
borderless
window of the same size on it). Next:
* if you don't need fast screen refresh, draw your bitmaps as normal (as
you would
in Blitz), then use BitMapToWindow to display them. This is slow and a
bit
flickery on AGA, probably worse on a graphics card
* an alternative method is to replace all your Blit calls with WBlit
calls, which
blit direct to the window. This can look ugly, unless you come up with
some way of
doing system friendly double buffering (something not many people on
this list
will have attempted, I think). Also you lose quite a bit of
functionality, as
there are no Window equivalents of Block, QBlit, BBlit (as far as I
know?).
* my preferred method, bearing in mind I was programming an OS version
for
graphics card users, is to transfer all your graphics operations to FAST
RAM,
using custom shape formats, a byte buffer instead of a bitmap, and some
custom ASM
routines I coded myself to replace the Blitter calls. Then you dump the
results of
your byte buffer to the window using WritePixelArray8_(). This method
was
suggested to me by Paul Burkey. It involves the most effort by far.
There are a few other considerations, such as will you make your program
entirely
event driven?
Hope this is of some help. If anyone would like to see the ASM routines
I
developed, let me know and I'll post them to this list,
    James

Jake Frederick wrote:

> Is it possible to make my blitz-mode game multi-tasking and OS
friendly
> without drastically changing the code? What are the major limitations
of using
> Amiga mode to make a game?
> --
>                                 -iF-
> -tHE dOORS oF pERCEPTION wERE cLEANSED eVERYTHING wOULD aPPEAR aS iT
