@NODE "Mail.418" "Re: Math Calculations"
From: Matt Daniels <mattd@underused.u-net.com>
Date: Wed, 04 Mar 1998 23:00:59 +0500
Subject: Re: Math Calculations

Hi Don, On 04-Mar-98 you wrote...

>Can Blitz do mathematical calculations of 14 significant figures or
>more?

The best blitz can do (out of the box) is a float, but it sounds like
you need double floats or better. I don`t know if anyone has written
a complex math lib, but if they haven`t you may have to create the
datatypes and math functions yourself :O If you are using this stuff
for work you will have to consider how stable your code will be.

>I need a large number of significant figures for engineering calculations
>involved in a program I would like to convert to BASIC language. If
>Blitz won't do it, does anyone have another suggestion that will?

INMHO Basic isn`t really the best thing to use for programs that are
maths intensive. Go for something like C or Pascal. If this program 
is already written in one of these then you may save yourself
some effort, if not cash.

Thanks
-- 
Matt Daniels
mattd@underused.u-net.com



