@NODE "Mail.421" "Make a much more powerfull Blitz 2"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 1998 19:05:58 +0100
Subject: Make a much more powerfull Blitz 2

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1746739232.1


    Hello Blitzers,

    I've know that a new Blitz like langage will be done in some times
(Phoenix) but for now I've a solution which could be very interresting.
Imagine, the Blitz 2 compiler itself is BUG FREE (That's TRUE !) so the '=
only'
thing we have to do is to add command to this compiler. The system to use=
 is
great, only do an function in ASM and do library. But the main drawback o=
f
this system is : if you include only 1 function, the WHOLE library will b=
e
included -> Dramatical size increaze. But, Hey, There is a VERY simple
solution : write only 1 command per library (Ok we will have lot of libra=
ry
(The same number that commands) but the size of exec will be EXACTLY what=
 it
should be...).

    I've begin this work by 'redo' the Len() function in ASM and do a lib=
rary
with it. I've use it and believe me or not (If not, install it and check =
;-),
the exec size is 2 time SHORTER !!! (1 kb instead of 2300 kb). And adding=
 the
NLen (NewLen) function to an program will only increase it's size of 100 =
bytes
instead of 1300kb. My Goal is to rewritten all the most used function (Wi=
th
your help ? Pleaaaaazzzzze ;-) to allow the Blitz 2 user to compile ULTRA=

SMALL proggy (ASM like...). For now Blitz 2 compiled program are big ;-).=
 The
functions I mean are :

    - Right$()
    - Left$()
    - Mid$()
    - Str$()
    - Val$()
    - Chr$()
    - Peek()
    - Poke()
     =

    Anyone is interrested ? I could be a killing features. And the blitz
library number can go up to 65000 so I think that we don't have more than=

65000 commands in Blitz ;-). If all goes well, we could remove the Old Bl=
itz 2
command and replace them by our new commands ! (We will keep exactly the =
same
name...). And we could fix some bugs too ;-)

    Regards,

        Fred.
    =

PS: I've attached the NLenLib.obj and the source code COMMENTED ;-). Just=
 try
it ! (Same usage than Len() but type NLen). If someone can optimize it to=
 the
max ;-)...
**=3D--------------------------------------------------------------------=
=3D**

                          -=3D>> AlphaSOUND <<=3D-

    Current Projects :     **  F-Base  2.30   **   [100 %] - Released -
                           **  F-Bench 1.20   **   [97  %]
                           **  TheBoss  1.00  **   [100 %] - Released -
                           **  Bomber Fighter **   [50  %]
                           **  ATD     2.00   **   [30  %]


                      =A9 1998 - Fantaisie Software -

                    *=3D- e-mail : alphasnd@hol.fr -=3D*

**=3D--------------------------------------------------------------------=
=3D**


