@NODE "Mail.447" "Re: Including Palette in Executable"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 03 Mar 1998 19:49:47 -0600
Subject: Re: Including Palette in Executable

Hi Tim,

On 03-Mar-98, Tim Johnson wrote:
>I have a small IFF file that I load to determine the palette of the game I'm
>working on.  What's the best way to include this file in the executable and
>make it load it from there once I finally get around to distributing the
game?

First, save just the palette itself in the directory with your source code.

Put this line near the top of your program:

DecodePalette 0,?gamepal
Use Palette 0


Then, near the bottom (after all executable program code):

.gamepal
IncBin "palettename"

When you compile your program, the palette will be included in your code, and
the Decode command will unpack it into a palette object when the program is
run.



-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
