@NODE "Mail.453" "Icons"
Date: 16 Mar 98 01:21:38 GMT
X-Plug: Xenolink, No. 1 BBS Software for the Amiga!
From: Simon Archer <bml@darkside.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Icons

On 14 Mar 98 Curt Esser wrote about 'Icons'.

 CE> Does anybody know about the DiskObject structure?


I've just recently gone through all this. It is really quite easy
to use the DiskObject structure but I couldn't find anyway of
transferring the image to a shape.

Once you've grabbed the DiskObject, like so:

*dobj.DiskObject = GetDiskObject("RAM:disk") ; (the .info will
                                    be automatically appended)

the *dobj structure contains a gadget structure:

*dobj.DiskObject\do_Gadget

and this in turn contains 2 image pointers:

*dobj.DiskObject\doGadget\GadgetRender
and *dobj.DiskObject\do_Gadget\SelectRender


each for the normal state and selected state of the gadgets.
The trick is to use these pointers (struct image) and put
them  into a shape object. I'm assuming thatthe shape object
has somewhere in it an image pointer. Maybe substituting these
would be enough?

I used DrawImageStatus_ to render the images into a window.
Alternatively, you could go the whole hog and use AddGadget_.

Simon Archer



