@NODE "Mail.470" "Re: GTSlider question"
	Sun, 29 Mar 1998 14:57:12 -0800 (PST)
From: BootBlock of Carnage <BootBlock@GeoCities.com>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 1998 16:30:18 GMT0
Subject: Re: GTSlider question

On 27-Mar-98, Krzysiek Jonko wibbled:

>I wonder how can I manualy change the slider position?
>GTSlider is set with any initial value first, then some part of program
>wants to "move" slider to another position.

I needed to use something like this a bit ago, it took me ages to figure out,
but here it is!

  #tag          = $80080000
  #GTSL_Level   = #tag+40

  GTSetAttrs  ListID,ID,#GTSL_Level,value


I think that's what you need.

>Thanks for your help Blitzers!

S'okay!

