@NODE "Mail.477" "Re: GTList"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 03 Mar 1998 20:01:59 -0600
Subject: Re: GTList

Hi Alan,

On 02-Mar-98, Liz Tucker wrote:
>Allan Pedersen wrote:
>> 

>> When i compile my program from TED there are problems. But then
>> when i run my created exe file this requester pops up. The
>> requester say's "GTList already attached to window!". Do anyone
>> know why this requester comes up? and how to get it fixed?
>>
>You will get this error if the window the GTList is trying to attach to
>hasn`t opened correctly for what ever reason so check the window is
>actually opening.

It is also possible that the GTlist really IS already attached.
If you open a window, attach the GTlist, and then close the window, you must
detach the GTlist before you open the same window again.
Or else you will get the error.
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



