@NODE "Mail.479" "Re: GTGetAttrs()"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 1998 16:10:01 -0600
Subject: Re: GTGetAttrs()

Hi Paul,

On 10-Mar-98, Paul Burkey wrote:
>Hi,

>Can anyone show me how to read the value of a GTSlider? I'm
>using GTGetAttrs(1,16,#GTSL_Level) and it doesn't seem to work.
>In the same program I'm using GTGetAttrs(1,13,#GTCY_Active)
>to read the value of a Cycle Gadget and that works fine but
>I'm having no luck with my slider.

I add $10 to my window's IDCMP to read mousemoves

Then use eventcode to read the slider when the event is $20:

If gadgethit=17    ;GTslider (with $80 added to read gadget down)
  Repeat           ;keep updating the volume
    ev.l=Event
    (stuff to update current volume display)
    vol=EventCode
  Until ev=$40     ;until the slider is released
EndIf

The GTGetAttrs may work also, if you add the $10 to the window, and $80 to the
GTslider.  But I don't think GTGetAttrs will work with OS 2.xx...

-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
