@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.487" "Re: Graphics cards and Vertical Blanks"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 1998 19:47:33 +0000
Subject: Re: Graphics cards and Vertical Blanks

Hi James,

> Can you use VWait and the Vertical Blank interrupt for
> a game that will run on graphics cards? How often do graphics cards
> generate Vertical Blanks? Does it vary between 50Hz and 60Hz, or is it
> exclusively one value?

VWait works in 50th of a second on my machine no matter what
GFX card screen mode I'm using. The AmigaOS call Delay_ does
exacly the same. I tested it with:

minute.l=50*60   ; 50 * 60 seconds
VWait minute

The result was a delay of 1 minute exactly according to my
trusty Sekonda :)

> Does it depend on the monitor/screen mode they are using?

The main screen mode I use is a 960x600x16 which runs at 48khz, 75hz.
The VWait call still works in 50ths of a second. Modules seem to
run at the same speed as they do in a PAL mode.

So in a nutshell... Don't worry about it! :) 

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://paulburkey.home.ml.org

