@NODE "Mail.503" "Re: GetaShape error?"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 1998 20:53:39 +0100
Subject: Re: GetaShape error?

Hi Frank,

> If I blit those grabbed shapes, some colours of them are missing (I mean
replaced
> with the transparent colour 0) and this appears completely randomly. But
sometimes
> the shapes have the right colors.

It's the old CPU cache problem. I think you can avoid this
bug by flushing the cpu caches after grabbing the shape.
I've never tried it myself but I think it's a simple OS call.
Try CacheClearE or CacheClearU or maybe someone knows the best
solution.

I only ever saw that bug when I was using an 030 for a short
period of time so it's not a bug I've can recreate on my 040.

Cheers,

Paul

