@NODE "Mail.504" "Re: GetAShape erro"
From: mike.child@sbu.ac.uk
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 1998 17:00:33 +0000
Subject: Re: GetAShape erro


Frank wrote:

>I have a problem with "GetaShape". Or is it the Blit/BBlit commands?

>If I blit those grabbed shapes, some colours of them are missing (I mean replaced
>with the transparent colour 0) and this appears completely randomly. But sometimes
>the shapes have the right colors.

>What am I doing wrong? Or again another stupid Blitz-error?
>BTW, Blitz or Amiga mode is the same with this. And it's even the same with sprites.

Yes I had this problem a while ago and it was discussed quite extensively on
the list.

The conclusion is that its a blitz bug that only affects 030's. Turning the
caches off solves it but thats not much use for general programming.

If you save your shapes after getting them, then immediately reload them before
trying to blit the problem is also solved. You should probably free them
between saving and loading to keep everything tidy.

You can save and load them to the RAM: disk which is pretty instant and avoids
writing to your HD.

Check the blitz-list archives for the previos discussion if you like, its on
Aminet and was included on Februarys AF CD (I think - might have been CU's CD
actually, I get em both)

Hope this helps 

Mike Child




