@NODE "Mail.505" "Genetic Programming"
From: C Dimitrakakis <cdimita@essex.ac.uk>
Subject: Genetic Programming
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 1998 23:18:13 +0100 (British Summer Time)
X-Authentication: IMSP

I have just made a Genetic Programming environment in Blitz Basic.
It uses a virtual machine (a simplified 68k) for program parsing and 
can process 1000 individuals in 3s on an 68030@50.
It really works too, as a demonstration of agents that evolve to be 
able to find the exit in a maze proves. (takes 10 to 30 generations for 
the gp to find an asm program that can solve a maze)
Mail me if you're interested in the .exe (20K .gz-ed)
I'll make the code available on Aminet under the terms of the GNU 
software license once I've cleaned it up and added documentation.



