@NODE "Mail.512" "FrontScreen command exists"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Sun, 08 Mar 1998 22:49:42 +0100
Subject: FrontScreen command exists

Hi,

After telling someone that the 'FrontScreen' command was likely
to be part of the standard AcidLibs file I was surprized that
only minutes later I recieved an email from Peter Thor claiming
he also was missing the FrontScreen command.

A little detection work revealed that the FrontScreen command
seems to have been added recently. It does exist in the
AcidLibs file which has been available on the RWE page for
quite some time though.

The exact location of the archive is:

http://www.ldngedge.demon.co.uk/Archives/acidlibs.lha

Anyone still using an old AcidLibs file should download this
version NOW! So if the FrontScreen command isn't available
to you then you must be using an old version of the acidlibs
file an updating to this version is advised.

Cheers,

