@NODE "Mail.513" "Re: Free GTList"
	Sun, 22 Mar 1998 03:47:58 -0800 (PST)
From: BootBlock of Carnage <BootBlock@GeoCities.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 1998 11:42:22 GMT0
Subject: Re: Free GTList

On 21-Mar-98, Frank Otto wibbled:
>Hello,

>how can I free a GTList attached to a window?

>"Free GTList" does not work, instead it causes a Recoverable Alert and
>crashes.

When you free a GTList, you must close the window FIRST and THEN free it,
like:

   CloseWindow 0
   Free GTList 0

If you have to free the list first, then try:

   DetachGTList 0
   Free GTList  0

This will let you still have the window open - you then can attach other
GTLists to the window.

