@NODE "Mail.518" "Re: Formost screen/Private screen"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 1998 19:06:45 -0600
Subject: Re: Formost screen/Private screen

Hi Andrew,

On 15-Mar-98, Andrew wrote:
>These answer have to be in Amiga mode.

>Is there any way of telling if a screen isn't the one showing as 
>the front screen any more?  I don't want other programs putting 
>the screen's on top of my screen.  I could of course keep putting 
>my screen to front but that uses to much CPU power up.

If you open your screen using a taglist, you can add the tag #SA_Exclusive to
prevent other screens from being pulled down to show your screen.  This also
prevents your screen from being pulled down.  This does NOT prevent your
screen from being pushed to the back.

You can use the FrontScreen command to check if your screen is in the front of
the display. 

>Is there any way of stopping any screen you have open with a 
>window on it which is active getting windows from other programs, 
>on to the screen you have opened?  This isn't a problem on 3.0 but 
>is on 3.1.

To make your screen private (nobody else can put a window on it):

Result=PubScreenStatus_(screen,#PSNF_PRIVATE)

after opening the screen.

You need Blitzlibs:Amigalibs.res in your compiler options for these constants.



                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



