@NODE "Mail.522" "Re: Font in RTEZRequest"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 04 Mar 1998 17:45:02 -0600
Subject: Re: Font in RTEZRequest

Hi,

On 04-Mar-98, Justin (TheCrow) wrote:
>When using the RTEZRequest command does anyone know if its possible to change
>the font within the requester (the message) to a proportional font?
>This is from an old program I did so I don't have much information about the
>command other than it has to be something to do with ReqTools, I cannot even
>find any documentation on this library, anywhere! :-(

Yes, this requestor and any other reqtools or asl requestors will
automatically use whatever your Intuifont is.  Just load the font you want to
use before you open your screen.

This command is from Neil's Reqtools Library, and the doc for it is in your
libs.dev.lha file.
-- 
