@NODE "Mail.525" "Re: File Types"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 1998 18:49:34 -0600
Subject: Re: File Types

Hi,

On 23-Mar-98, Paul Burkey wrote:
>Hi Oliver,

>> Anyone know how to test a file to see what format it is saved as
>> because i want to test all files in a directory and display only iff
>> picture filenames.

>Check the first 4 characters of the file for the characters 'FORM'.
>Then if it exists you can then check for the existance of the
>characters 'ILBM' which should appear soon after. The existance
>of both FORM and ILBM will confirm it's probably an iff picture.

>A shorter version would be to check for 'ILBM' starting at byte 8.
>I'm not sure if that is standard but it looks good to me :)

Yes, this is standard ^^ But you must read starting at byte 9  :)
It should be "FORMxxxxILBM...."

I sent an example to Aminet/dev/basic called "Optimized.Remap".  Although it
is intended to show how to remap a picture's colours to the workbench, it also
contains code for identifying iff pictures.  It also recognizes GIF, JPEG, and
IFF Animation files, and can identify HAM and TrueColour (24 bit) pictures.
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



