@NODE "Mail.531" "Re: FDConvert"
From: "Julian Kinraid" <jkinraid@clear.net.nz>
Subject: Re: FDConvert
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 1998 11:19:18 +1200
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi James,

>Can anybody explain EXACTLY how to use FDConvert?
>
>I'm just messing about,but I can't get it to convert any
>fd files...
>
>I've made the executable file,but I'm not sure what to supply
>as parameters (I get "Can't open noname" or something).
>
>Can somebody say exactly what to do to convert an fd file for
>Blitz use?


You supply the name of the fd file (including the path) as the =
parameter.  'FDConvert FD:Graffiti_lib.fd'.  Then you will be asked to =
type in a library number to use.  It should suggest a number, so just =
type that in.

