@NODE "Mail.548" "Re: Dpf_cols"
From: Mark Thompson <mark@sleepy.u-net.com>
Date: Tue, 03 Mar 1998 01:40:05 -0000
Subject: Re: Dpf_cols


>Hi All,
>       I have now rewritten display routines on my platform game using the
>display.library (Cheers, Paul!)

>But the backdrop colours are getting messed up. I am blitting 8col shapes
>to the fg bitmap (maybe I should be using sprites?) So I load in the
>palette as the shapes palette, and then the backdrop palette with the
>offset 8, but with a 64 colour backdrop, some of the colours get screwed
>up. e.g My nice yellow sun suddenly turns light blue.

>I've tried everything I can think of!

>Can anyone help? It's the final routine I need to fix to complete the
>game!

>Thanks a lot

>Duncan



Hi Duncan,

I hit the very same problem while writing a Dual Playfield scrolling
routine. Anyway, I pulled the following lines out of that code but
it's been a while since I looked at this. As far as I can remember
the DisplayControls line is the important one. It sets up
BPLCON3 which tells AGA which palette banks to use. I wish I'd
commented my code now but $d00 worked for me. Give it a try.

InitCopList 0,#screen_start,#screen_height,$10038,8,32,5

DisplayControls 0,0,$d00,0

DisplayPalette 0,0

DisplayAdjust 0,0,0,0,0,0

CreateDisplay 0



Good luck,

Mark



