On  2 Apr 98 at 5:58, C Dimitrakakis opened wide and rumbled:

> I have a problem with my graphics.library1 and graphics.library2 files..
> commands in graphics.library2 are tokenized to graphics.library1 
> commands. (ie BestModeIDA_ is tokenized to AreaErase_). I think this 
> happenned after I used fdconvert and makedeflibs... I used libnumbers 
> 254 and 254 for both... should've worked!

 I think you can just use fdconvert again on the graphics.library and 
just give them two different numbers then run makedeflibs again. 
Failing that, delete the graphics.library1 and graphics.library2 
files from Blitzlibs:<wherever>, run makedeflibs then use fdconvert 
(using two different libnums) and run makedeflibs.


