@NODE "Mail.562" "Re: Clipping?"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 1998 06:07:21 -0600
Subject: Re: Clipping?

Hi Chris,

On 12-Mar-98, Chris Jonko wrote:
>Hi!
>I wonder how to load picture GREATER than window as a window background
>(unnecessary borders should be cutted). Of course it SHOULD work on
>graphics card too 8)

Just use BitMapToWindow using the optional parameters to cut the picture size.

For example, to center a picture that is 640*400 in a window that is 600*360:

Load the picture to a 640*400 bitmap
then use:

BitMapToWindow,Bitmap#,Window#,20,20,0,0,600,400

This trims 20 pixels off each side of the picture.

This will work on both GFX card systems, and non-GFX card if I have understood
the GFC card discussions correctly, although it is not the best way for GFX
cards since it uses some chip memory for the bitmap.

Bye...

                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
