@NODE "Mail.569" "Chunky CPUBlit Benchmarks"
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 1998 10:28:05 +0100
From: James Marshall <homegrown@eclipse.co.uk>
Subject: Chunky CPUBlit Benchmarks

Hello everyone,
  I decided to run some speed tests on my CPU chunky blit commands, here
are the results. In each case I'm blitting a 256 colour 64x32 shape to a
256 colour bitmap 1000 times. I also compare like with like as far as
possible (except for cpu_block/Block). All tests were done on a Blizzard
1230-IV (68030@50Mhz), with 8MB FAST RAM.

Block: 1000 shapes in 62 ticks=16.1 shapes per tick
cpu_block: 1000 shapes in 71 ticks=14.1 shapes per tick
NOTE: Block is optimised for word aligned blitting, the cpu_block
routine is not (does anyone know how to do that?)

Blit: 1000 shapes in 149 ticks=6.7 shapes per tick
cpu_blit: 1000 shapes in 93 ticks=10.8 shapes per tick

ClipBlit: 1000 shapes in 152 ticks=6.6 shapes per tick
cpu_clipblit: 1000 shapes in 91 ticks=10.9 shapes per tick

So, as you can see, my routines are generally 50+% faster than their
blitter counterparts on an 030@50Mhz. The results showing cpu_clipblit
to be slightly faster than cpu_blit were surprising considering the
extra computation required, but I confirmed the results with an
additional run of 10000 blits.
    James

--
Homegrown Software - Independent Amiga Games Developers
Web - http://www.eclipse.co.uk/homegrown
email - homegrown@eclipse.co.uk




@ENDNODE
