@NODE "Mail.604" "BlitzPPC and more"
From: Andreas =?iso-8859-1?Q?H=E5kansson?= <andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 1998 17:36:48 +0100
Subject: BlitzPPC and more



 Hiya,

Well it's about time we stoped talking about what a great idea it would
be  to  email  acid  (or  who ever owns the rights to Blitz Basic), and
actually do it. We need to decide what we sould  put  in  the  mail  to
start  of  with.  I  think it's important that we write it so that acid
will realise that they actually could make much  more  money  on  Blitz
Basic,  if they gave a group of people the right to edit the main blitz
code.

I dont think we should as them to sell the source code to us, but point
out  that if they keeps the legal rights to blitz basic, but still gave
the code to someone to bring it up to date, that this would  mean  more
money  to  them,  without  any  work at all (besides some legal work to
write up somekind of contract or what ever, with the  people  that  get
the source codem so that acid knows that the source wont be spread).

The "rebirth" that AMOS is about to start, is  also  a  very  important
thing  to  tell  them  about.  If AMOS gets this face lift before blitz
basic does, then they wont make  any  money  of  blitz  anymore,  since
people would sawp to amos.

PPC support is also something that they  must  been  told  about.  Once
again it's very important to get, since the ppc has been choosen as the
new official cpu for the amiga, and if blitz donesn't support it,  they
might  as  well blow up the source code, and any hope of every making a
few bucks of it. Once again we should mention that amos is getting  ppc
support.  Perhaps we should tell them about RWE's project to give blitz
ppc support, and that making somekind of deal with RWE about the source
code, would speed up this very much.

I know that there are much more to bring up, like AHI, RTG etc, but you
can  write  down  what  you  think  should  be said about all the other
things, and post it here on the list, and I will make a summary of them
all.  More importently, who should Acid make a deal with conserning the
source code then? RWE?. As most of us know it's only Steve  thats  left
in RWE, and it's alot of work for him, since he has a real job as well.

Therefor I have a serious suggestion to make, that I ask of all to read
threw  and  tell me what you think. I think we should setup somekind of
blitz committee, that takes a professional approche to help bring blitz
into  the  next  century.  This  committiee  would be somekind of blitz
standard committee, that would work toward making  blitz  the  ultimate
basic  language  on the amiga system. People could send thier ideas for
improving blitz (new ideas, and bug rapports).  To  start  of  with  we
wouldn't  do  any  of  programming  to improve blitz, but the committee
could work toward getting acid  releasing  the  source  to  someone  (a
group),  that  could  improve  blitz.  Once this is done, the committee
would work close together with that group, and help  them  as  much  as
possible. This would make work much easier for the group as well, since
they wouldnt have to think about getting bug rapport, and new ideas for
features,  it  would  all  be take care of the committee, which in turn
would informe the  group.  Well  I  have  loads  more  ideas  for  this
committee,  that  I will present if you guys think this would be a good
idea. Some of them are that it should be an  elected  group  of  people
that sit on the "board", later on the committe could form workgroups to
write applications, libs etc, to  help  make  the  making  of  programs
easier  to  the  blitz  users (such things like mapeditor, shape/sprite
editors, etc)

We also should get in contact with Steve from RWE to ask  him  what  he
things  about  this.  I've  currently  only heard from 12 people on the
blitz lits (including my self), that  things  that  we  should  try  to
convince acid to "license" the source to someone that could improve it.
I wont add anyone to the list that hasn't shown intresste to  this.  We
need  much  more people to add to the list, I would think that everyone
on the blitz mailing list would help to do this, so if your  intressted
then  email me and tell me, and I will add you. And tell you friends to
contact me aswell if they are  intressted.  I  wont  add  anyone,  that
deosnt  have  an  email adress (like some one saying "HEy add my friend
Jack Smith to the list, he thinks  it's  a  great  idea"),  since  acid
should have the possibility to email anyone thats "signed" the list, to
veriefy that they have  "signed"  it.  Otherwize  they  wont  take  use
seriously. Here is the current list of people that has "signed"

    Mike Carter         <57229007@mmu.ac.uk>
