My two cents (or pennies) worth:
  It would be nice if the name for the committee was in the old Acid
tradition (ie: like the acronym BUM :)

  If we do a new language (good idea), how is going to be done? Do we
end up with a commercial product- then who gets the money, or allocates
the profits? =

   Or will it be like the GeekGadgets thing, and everyone contributes,
and it's free to everyone? - Something to think about.

  Another important thing that needs to be done somewhere along the line
is Internet code. Paul has already started this off well, with TCP and
Server/Client code examples, and a good dedicated webpage. I've been
researching UDP Peer to Peer connections- useful for high speed reaction
games (like Quake, platformers etc). I almost have this ready to put
into a small demo 2d game (work is delayed at the moment though :-/
  I'm willing to give Blitz my routines when I'm happy with them- that
way people can chuck those routines directly into their game (as long as
it multitasks), and have instant Internet multiplayer connectivity- Suck
on that AM*OS!!
  Maybe later the routines could get put into a library for easy use
etc. And also LAN support could be put in for connected Amigas (they
could be connected to other players on the Internet at the same time as
well).

