@NODE "Mail.623" "Blitz Committee"
          Wed, 18 Mar 1998 14:22:43 +0100 (MET)
From: Peter Thor <thor@mailbox.swipnet.se>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 14:23:40 -0500
Subject: Blitz Committee

Hi Blitzers!
 
I think the idea of a Blitz Committee where the future development of Blitz
will be looked upon is a great one. This could  be something similar to ICOA
as stated. It is too good to just be thrown into the sea, lets do something
while we still can and have support (from inside the community).

Some things to consider  support for are GFX Boards (eg. RTG etc), AHI etc - 
i guess you all know what im talking about. We need to push the limits - both
for the language itself (or whatever it will become) and add support for
upcoming standards. Maybe we could contact ICOA about this, i guess there are
ppl in this list who's got positions and acccess to that organisations
descitions etc.

A professional homepage is essential - with support and help for
users/beginners. News sections and so forth which makes it look more stable
and something to consider.

The fact that AMOS is getting back into dev is something we should have in
mind, it is still a rough language, but with its likenings and advantages. The
time must be utilised.

I think the work from RWE should be something to lean back upon  and push
forward - PPC Development. This it just a must. Another thing is Network
Support. With the future who most likely looks to require more and more
connected computers and networked applications, blitz should support this
(though maybe via the OS when AI gives the community their specifications
about their next version of the AOS)

Improvments in all fields are required, therefor i strongly support Andreas
idea about a Blitz Committee.

Let's draw out the guidelines for the homepage and its major points, then lets
consider who should be deticated and involved into the committee.
Now we might be moving somewhere... =)

//Thor
