@NODE "Mail.624" "Blitz CodeStats - yet another binary posting :)"
From: Paul Burkey <paul@sneech.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 1998 15:25:45 +0000
Subject: Blitz CodeStats - yet another binary posting :)

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1747735384.2

Hi,

This may annoy some and please others. Yes it's a binary file!
Well, Aminet is not working properly so I couldn't upload it
there. My web page is full and I thought this may be usefull
to quite a few people. One thing I can't stand is when I'm
reading some mail/news off-line and someone tells me about
a program that may be usefull. I'm forced to go back on-line
to search for it. Finding the program is already sitting on
my HD is much better! :)

It basicly creates some rough statistics on the commands
and libraries used by your source code. Simply save your
code as an ascii file and type: CodeStats <source.asc>

It'll give you a listing of the libs used, what commands are
used, total size of libs used, total count of commands called.

It's far from perfect, it only knows about "real libs" so
no .library .resource calls are logged. This was done to
keep the file size down because it's using an internal list
of libs and commands created from *my* setup. If you're
using JoeBlogsLib.obj then it won't detect it. I'll create
a bigger internal database of libs when I update the program
but my lib collection is fairly good including all the BSS
stuff. 

The program even knows the names and sizes of the Acid libs
so you'll get some fairly informative results. Tokenized source
support is possbile in a future update but I'd have to write
some prety good acidlibs/deflibs parsing. The lib name isn't
stored in the deflibs file so this also makes it less informative.

Anyway, I hope some find it usefull. When Aminet is working
properly I'll upload a better version with more libs included
as well as a small utility that will create your own personal
libs database.

Cheers

-- 
Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
http://paulburkey.home.ml.org

--BOUNDARY.1747735384.2
