From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 1998 17:57:22 -0600
Subject: Re: Binaries

Hi,

On 25-Mar-98, Donovan Reeve wrote:
>On 22-Mar-98, BootBlock of Carnage flashed:

>>>>some people like me don't mind getting the occassional binary file 
>>>>especially when it's relevent to the list subject in this case blitz

>>>I really don't mind getting binaries in my emailbox.  I have a 28.8k modem,
>>>getting 15k from a POP server does not take up too much of my time.

>>Nope, I don't mind either. The whole point is to help each other out and
>share
>>code, so anyone feel free to email me those binaries with that luverly Blitz
>>type code in `em!

>  I not only don't mind, I appreciate it!  It's great to have helpful stuff
>show up in my e-mail.  It sure beats all the junk mail and gripes.
>  Several programs which have showed up as an answer to somebody else have
>given me new ideas and/or solved problems for me.

Yes, I agree.  I probably have learned more from seeing the answer to other
people's questions and example codes than from my own questions.  It is always
good to see other people's ideas and codes.  It makes me think of things I
never would have on my own.

And I don't remember ever getting any excessively large emails from this list.

So I say, send them along if they are small.  If it is a full, working example
of something, it should also be sent to dev/basic so everyone can access it
when they need it.

-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
