@NODE "Mail.643" "Backward Calculation"
Subject: Backward Calculation
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 1998 12:10:00 +0000 (GMT)
From: "Adam Lounds" <adaml@tcp.net.uk>

> Hi all,
> 
> I am using a GTslider to allow the user to set a size for rescaling a picture.
>  The slider controls the x dimension, the y dimension is calculated by using
> the original picture's proportions.  I need to limit the slider so the new
> picture will fit in the available chip ram.
> 
> It is easy enough to do this after the user selects a size:
> 
> for example:
> 
> x size=500
> scale=2
> depth=8
> 
> x*(x*scale)*depth/8=500,000 bytes needed
> 
> But I need to calculate the maximum x size before creating the gadget.
> 
> I know scale, depth, and bytes available.
> 
> Can someone tell me how to find x from this?

Sorry if this looks wrong - I'm not too good at replying to mailing
lists.

I think you got confused when you put the x*scale in brackets.
If you try x*x*scale*depth/8 = size, then rearranging gives

maxsize*8 / (depth*scale) = x^2

do a square root to find x.

(Check it out with your own figures: 500000*8 / (8*2) = 250000
25000 = 500^2)

HTH
--
Adam Lounds                     | Email: adaml@tcp.net.uk
Network Assistant               | Tel: +44 1703 571300
Total Connectivity Providers    | WWW: http://www.tcp.co.uk/


@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.644" "Backward Calculation"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 1998 05:51:33 -0600
Subject: Backward Calculation

Hi all,

I am using a GTslider to allow the user to set a size for rescaling a picture.
 The slider controls the x dimension, the y dimension is calculated by using
the original picture's proportions.  I need to limit the slider so the new
picture will fit in the available chip ram.

It is easy enough to do this after the user selects a size:

for example:

x size=500
scale=2
depth=8

x*(x*scale)*depth/8=500,000 bytes needed

But I need to calculate the maximum x size before creating the gadget.

I know scale, depth, and bytes available.

Can someone tell me how to find x from this?

Thanks for your help
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.645" "Re: Backward Calculation"
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 1998 13:28:48 +0100
From: Philippe Socias <psocias@microresearch.be>
Subject: Re: Backward Calculation

Curt Esser wrote:

> ...

> x size=500
> scale=2
> depth=8
>
> x*(x*scale)*depth/8=500,000 bytes needed
>
> But I need to calculate the maximum x size before creating the gadget.
>
> I know scale, depth, and bytes available.
>
> Can someone tell me how to find x from this?
>
> ...

If your formula is right, then

x=sqrt( 8*bytes_available / scale*depth )

('sqrt' is for square root, I don't remember in which form it is available in
Blitz)

--
Philippe Socias - MailTo:psocias@microresearch.be




@ENDNODE
