@NODE "Mail.648" "Re: AVI/MPEG"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 1998 19:15:39 +0100
Subject: Re: AVI/MPEG

Hi,

>     does anyone know how I can use blitz to launch an AVI/MPEG
> animation engine to play anims?

You can use the Execute_ or Run commands to launch anything you want.

> Also does anyone know how to include sound to MPEG/AVI animations?

MPEGs and AVI's often have sound built into them but the Amiga
isn't powerful enough to play sound *and* mpeg/avi correctly unless
you've got PPC. The Amiga has trouble playing MPEG sound by itself
never mind with mpeg video at the same time :)

The alternative is to play huge samples direct from the HD or
to play modules as you mentioned.

> That would also be cool, as using Meds would slow the rate down,
> and I've ben haveing trouble with MODS recently

I don't have any problems with the XbonesCIATrkLib.

Cheers,

Paul

