@NODE "Mail.649" "Asm line counter thing"
From: BootBlock of Carnage <BootBlock@GeoCities.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Sep 2009 04:32:59 GMT0
Subject: Asm line counter thing

Has anyone got any suggestions on how to make this faster? All it does is
count how many Carriage Returns are in the specified memory block (usually a
textfile that has been read in with ReadMem).

a0   =   Start of memory block
d0   =   Length (in bytes) of memory block

    GetReg  a0,ptr
    GetReg  d0,flen

    MOVE.l  #0,d1
    MOVE.l  #0,d4
_jump:
    MOVE.b  (a0),d3
    CMP.b   $0a,d3
    BNE    _jump2
    ADDQ.l  #1,d4
_jump2:
    ADDQ.l  #1,d1
    ADDQ.l  #1,a0
    MOVE.l  d1,d2
    CMP.l   d2,d0
    BNE    _jump

    PutReg d4,lines

    Dim    Article$(lines)

Also, does anyone know how I can format a block of memory (containing the
above textfile) and put it into an array as fast as possible?

Thanks for any help!

-- 
