@NODE "Mail.650" "Re: Asm line counter thing"
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <samin@megabaud.fi>
Date: Sun, 08 Mar 1998 16:06:19 +0200
Subject: Re: Asm line counter thing

On 10-Sep-09, BootBlock of Carnage wrote:
> Has anyone got any suggestions on how to make this faster? All it does =
is
> count how many Carriage Returns are in the specified memory block (usua=
lly a
> textfile that has been read in with ReadMem).

> a0   =3D   Start of memory block
> d0   =3D   Length (in bytes) of memory block

>     GetReg  a0,ptr
>     GetReg  d0,flen

>     MOVE.l  #0,d1
>     MOVE.l  #0,d4
> _jump:
>     MOVE.b  (a0),d3
>     CMP.b   $0a,d3
>     BNE    _jump2
>     ADDQ.l  #1,d4
> _jump2:
>     ADDQ.l  #1,d1
>     ADDQ.l  #1,a0
>     MOVE.l  d1,d2
>     CMP.l   d2,d0
>     BNE    _jump

>     PutReg d4,lines

>     Dim    Article$(lines)

> Also, does anyone know how I can format a block of memory (containing t=
he
> above textfile) and put it into an array as fast as possible?

You meant LineFeeds :) not CRs

Ok here it's in optimized form.
there is one way of doing it faster but it will restrict the file size
as smaller than 65536 bytes (the later example)

     GetReg  a0,ptr
     GetReg  d0,flen

     MOVE.l a0,a1
     ADD.l  d0,a1
     ADDQ.l #1,a1
     MOVEQ  #0,d1
     MOVEQ  #10,d0
_jump:
     CMP.b   d0,(a0)+
     BNE    _jump2
     ADDQ.l  #1,d1
_jump2:
     CMPA   a1,a0
     BNE    _jump

     PutReg d1,lines

     Dim    Article$(lines)

file size smaller than 65536 bytes

     GetReg  a0,ptr
     GetReg  d0,flen

     subq.l #1,d0
     MOVEQ  #0,d2
     moveq  #10,d1
_jump:
     CMP.b   d1,(a0)+
     BNE    _jump2
     ADDQ.l  #1,d2
_jump2:
     dbra   d0,_jump

     PutReg d2,lines

     Dim    Article$(lines)

         _____________________________________________________
        |                                                     |
        |  Sami N=E4=E4t=E4nen   A1260 20MB 2.5GB 2X 56k BJC-4100   |
        |  EMail: samin@megabaud.fi                           |
        |                                                     |
        `-----------------------------------------------------'



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.651" "Re: AppMsgPort command"
From: "Julian Kinraid" <jkinraid@clear.net.nz>
Subject: Re: AppMsgPort command
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 1998 15:42:12 +1200
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi Luca,


>Hi Blitzers and especially Julian Kinraid,

>I'm using the Acidlibs fixed by you, Julian, (I suppose you fixed it) but
the
>AppMsgPort command is disappeared (I just see a "?????" instead) and I'm
not
>able to code AppIcons any more.  Could you explain why?


It's those luverly library numbers.  When you upgraded your acidlibs, the
library number for the library containing 'AppMsgPort' changed.  Because
of the way Blitz tokenises source code, when a library number changes,
you'll end up getting wierd results.

For the record, the tiny change I made to the acidlibs (which is the one
on the RWE web site), will have no effect on the end user (apart from the
bug fix.)

>I have to use the following line:

>  AddWaitEvent PortSigBit(AppMsgPort),$800000


I suggest going back to your old acidlibs, save your code in ASCII format,
then use the new acidlibs.

Hopefully that clears things up.

Ciao,
Julian Kinraid



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.652" "AppMsgPort command"
From: Luca Carminati <toffi@spm.it>
Date: Mon, 04 Sep 1995 12:12:26 -0500
Subject: AppMsgPort command

