@NODE "Mail.670" "Re: AHI_Library Update."
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 1998 13:12:37 +0000
From: Paul Lathwell <paul@blitzer.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: AHI_Library Update.


Okay, I put my hand up - it was me whom complained about the binary
postings to this list. My reasons...

1. The more people post binaries to a mailing list others will also think
it a good idea and before long everyone is posting their latest 10-15k
wonder routine. Problem is there may only be a small number of people
interested in the code.

2. It`s generally accepted that posting binaries to mailing lists is a bit
of a no-no, there are plenty of newsgroups for this purpose already, and as
has already been pointed out Aminet is the ideal place for example code.
Just post the filename and placement of the file and those that want it can
get it. :)

3. People will complain when binaries are attached, and then you end up
with crap like this being posted trying to find an agreement on what should
be allowed or not. :(

4. This one may be a little more personal to myself - Not all people using
this list are using Amiga`s to do so. I`m in the position of using a PC and
there are two reasons why I still take this mailing list. 1. I`m interested
in any news of a PC version of Blitz. 2. This one is more important - I
hope to be able to offer some help from my own Blitz experience where I can.

Now, if the general opinion is that binary attachments to this list is
going to be acceptable then I`ll quite happily leave this list and let you
get on with it. It`s really up to the majority IMO.


-- 
Bye now...
