@NODE "Mail.675" "AHI into Blitz 2 is no more a dream !"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 21:45:59 +0100
Subject: AHI into Blitz 2 is no more a dream !


    Hi Blitzers !

    After reading all the messages posted to this list, two things come b=
ack
often : The lacks of AHI support and a good RTG support. Be happy blitz c=
oders
because I've converted the AHI system to work with Blitz 2 ! And all is
possible (The device is fully converted, includes files too). All the
programming is done with the help of simple functions (AHI_Init{},
AHI_LoadSound{Name} (Support IFF/Raw Files, may be more (not tested)),
AHI_PlaySound{SoundID, Length, Asynchrone Yes/No} The Asynchrone flag is =
to
play sound in the background (very useful for a game) and AHI_Close{}.

    Anyone interessed ? (Paul : Fundation support AHI ? If not, it's may =
be
the solution ;-)

        Fred.

PS : In the same style, I've converted the XPK library (fully), StoneTrac=
ker
libray (fully), Lowlevel (a bit), GtLayout (some calls).
Yes I'm a crazy lib convertor ;-).
