@NODE "Mail.682" "Re: ActiveScreen vs FrontScreen"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 1998 18:14:28 -0600
Subject: Re: ActiveScreen vs FrontScreen

On 13-Mar-98, Mathias Parnaudeau wrote:
>Hello,

>I read the discuss about ActiveScreen and FrontScreen.
>I wrote a program to understand the problem, then :

>1. Like MinuteMan2026, my Blitz doesn't recognize the FrontScreen
>function.

If you get the new acidlibs file Paul recommended, it will.

>2. ActiveScreen seems to always send the Wb screen address, even if this
>screen is behind or other.

The last screen you used is always the "Active" screen, until you left-click
on the new screen.

>Anyway, is there a real difference between an active screen and a front
>screen ?

Yes - try this:

Load PPaint or some other program that uses it's own screen and it's own
mousepointer.

Now push this screen to the back.  You will see Workbench, but until you click
on it with the mouse button, you still see PPaint's pointer.

This is because PPaint is still the "Active" screen although you can't see it.
 WorkBench is now the "Front" screen but not the "Active" screen.

When you click on it, WorkBench is now the "Active" screen and also the
"Front" screen.

Now push WorkBench to the back.  Here is PPaint again.  Try to use the menus
before clicking the left button on PPaint's screen.  They don't work, because
WorkBench is still the "Active" screen until you left-click on the PPaint
screen.

I hope this explains it.  

                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.683" "ActiveScreen vs FrontScreen"
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 1998 18:44:01 +0100 (MET)
From: Mathias Parnaudeau <mathias@pegase.univ-angers.fr>
Subject: ActiveScreen vs FrontScreen

Hello,

I read the discuss about ActiveScreen and FrontScreen.
I wrote a program to understand the problem, then :

1. Like MinuteMan2026, my Blitz doesn't recognize the FrontScreen
function.

2. ActiveScreen seems to always send the Wb screen address, even if this
screen is behind or other.

Anyway, is there a real difference between an active screen and a front
screen ?

Thanks...

=09=09Mathias


* Mathias PARNAUDEAU *
mathias@pegase.univ-angers.fr

- Lisez AMIGAzette - Read AMIGAzette - L=EA AMIGAzette -




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.684" "Re: ActiveScreen vs FrontScreen"
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 1998 22:02:54 +0100
Subject: Re: ActiveScreen vs FrontScreen

Hi Mathias,

> 1. Like MinuteMan2026, my Blitz doesn't recognize the FrontScreen
> function.

Grab the a newer version of acidlibs from the RWE web page. Just
follow the the archives links. I'd imgine the size of the newer
acidlibs file is much different to your present one 50k ??
Which makes me think it's worth replacing :)

> 2. ActiveScreen seems to always send the Wb screen address, even if this
> screen is behind or other.

Does your screen have a Window on it? Maybe it needs a Window to become
active or something. Similar to the way Worbench always has a window
open too.
 
> Anyway, is there a real difference between an active screen and a front
> screen ?

Not much of a difference really. I can think of very few important
reasons why you could use one as apposed to the other. Use the
one that fits your needs!

Cheers,

Paul

